  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Last Days"
      title: "David\u2019s Last Days"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now King David had become old, advanced in years, and they covered
        him with garments, but he was not warm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "His servants said to him, \u201CLet them search for a young virgin
        for my lord the king, and let her stand before the king. Let her be of use
        for him, and let her lie in your lap that my lord the king may be warm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they sought a beautiful young woman in all the territory of Israel,
        and they found Abishag the Shunnamite and brought her to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Adonijah Seeks David\u2019s Throne"
      title: "Adonijah Seeks David\u2019s Throne"
      number: 4
      content: 'Now the young woman was very beautiful; she was of use for the king,
        and she served him, but the king did not have sexual relations with her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now Adonijah the son of Haggith was exalting himself, saying, \u201CI
        will be king,\u201D so he prepared for himself a chariot and horsemen and
        fifty men running before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "His father did not rebuke him at any time by saying, \u201CWhy did
        you do so?\u201D Now he was also very handsome of appearance; she had borne
        him after Absalom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah and with Abiathar the priest,
        and they supported Adonijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Zadok the priest, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, Nathan the prophet,
        Shimei, Rei, and the mighty warriors were David\u2019s; they were not with
        Adonijah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Adonijah sacrificed sheep, oxen, and fattened animals near the
        stone of Zoheleth, which is beside En Rogel. He invited all of his brothers,
        the sons of the king, and all the men of Judah, the servants of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Solomon\u2019s Intercessors"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Intercessors"
      number: 10
      content: 'But he did not invite Nathan the prophet or Benaiah or the mighty
        warriors or Solomon his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Nathan said to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, \u201CHave you
        not heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith has become king, but our lord
        David does not know? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So then, come, let me advise you please, that you may save your life
        and the life of your son, Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Come, go to King David and say to him, \u2018Have you not, my lord
        the king, sworn to your servant, \u201CSurely Solomon your son shall become
        king after me. And he will sit on my throne\u201D? But why is Adonijah king?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "While you are still there speaking with the king, I will enter after
        you, and I will confirm your words.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Bathsheba went to the king in the private room. Now the king was
        very old, and Abishag the Shunnamite was attending the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Bathsheba knelt and bowed down before the king, and the king asked,
        \u201CWhat do you want?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "She said to him, \u201CMy lord, you swore by Yahweh your God to your
        servant, \u2018Solomon your son surely shall become king after me, and he
        will sit upon my throne!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But now, look! Adonijah has become king! And now, my lord the king,
        you do not know! '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He has sacrificed oxen and sheep and fattened animals in abundance,
        and he has invited all the sons of the king, Abiathar the priest, Joab the
        commander of the army, but Solomon your servant he did not invite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But as for you, my lord the king, the eyes of all of Israel are on
        you, to tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "It shall be that when my lord the king sleeps with his ancestors,
        I and my son Solomon will be considered as sinners.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'While she was still speaking with the king, Nathan the prophet came
        in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They told the king, \u201CNathan the prophet is here.\u201D He came
        into the presence of the king and bowed down before the king with his face
        to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Nathan said, \u201CMy lord the king, have you said, \u2018Adonijah
        shall be king after me and he shall sit on my throne\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CFor he went down today and sacrificed oxen, sheep, and fattened
        animals in abundance. He invited all the sons of the king, the commanders
        of the army, and Abiathar the priest, and look, they are eating and drinking
        before him. They have also said, \u201CLong live King Adonijah! "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But me, your servant, Zadok the priest, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada,
        and Solomon your servant he did not invite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If it was from my lord the king that this thing has happened, then
        all is well, but if not, you must let your servants know who shall sit on
        the throne of my lord the king after him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then King David answered and said, \u201CSummon Bathsheba for me.\u201D
        Then she came before the king and stood in his presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then the king swore and said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, who has saved
        my life from all trouble, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "surely as I swore to you by Yahweh the God of Israel, saying, \u2018Solomon
        your son shall surely be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne in
        my place,\u2019 surely I shall do so this very day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Solomon Is Crowned King'
      title: Solomon Is Crowned King
      number: 31
      content: "Then Bathsheba knelt with her face to the ground and did obeisance
        to the king, and she said, \u201CMay my lord, King David, live forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then King David said, \u201CSummon Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet,
        and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada,\u201D and they came before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The king said to them, \u201CTake with you all the servants of your
        lord, and let them make Solomon my son ride on my mule, and bring him down
        to Gihon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anoint him there as king
        over Israel. Blow on the trumpet and say, \u2018Long live King Solomon!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then you shall go up after him, and let him come and sit on my throne;
        he shall be king in my place. I have appointed him to be leader over Israel
        and Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king and said, \u201CAmen!
        So may Yahweh, the God of my lord the king, confirm it! "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "As Yahweh was with my lord the king, so may he be with Solomon and
        make his throne greater than the throne of my lord King David.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada,
        the Kerethites, and the Pelethites went down, and they let Solomon ride on
        the mule of King David, and they brought him to Gihon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Zadok the priest took the horn of oil from the tent, and he
        anointed Solomon. They blew on the trumpet, and all the people said, \u201CLong
        live King Solomon!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "40: Adonijah\u2019s Response to the Coronation of Solomon"
      title: "Adonijah\u2019s Response to the Coronation of Solomon"
      number: 40
      content: 'All the people went up after him, and the people were playing on
        the flutes and rejoicing with great joy, and the earth shook with their noise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And Adonijah and all the invited guests who were with him heard it.
        Now they were finished eating when Joab heard the sound of the trumpet and
        said, \u201CWhy is there such a noise in the city?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "While he was still speaking, suddenly Jonathan the son of Abiathar
        the priest came. Adonijah said, \u201CCome, for you are a man of valor, and
        you bring good news.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Jonathan answered and said to Adonijah, \u201CBut our lord King David
        has made Solomon king! "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "He sent Zadok the priest with the king, and Nathan the prophet, Benaiah
        the son of Jehoiada, the Kerethites, and the Pelethites; they made him ride
        on the king\u2019s mule. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anointed him as king at Gihon,
        and they have gone up from there rejoicing. The city has gone wild; this
        is the sound which you heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And also, Solomon sits on the throne of the kingdom! '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "The servants of the king also came to congratulate our lord King
        David, saying, \u2018Your God has made the name of Solomon better than your
        name and his throne greater than your throne!\u2019 So the king worshiped
        on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "What is more, the king said, \u2018May Yahweh the God of Israel be
        blessed, who has given this day one sitting on my throne, and my eyes are
        seeing it!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Then all the invited guests who were for Adonijah trembled and got
        up and went, each on his way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Adonijah was afraid because of Solomon, and he got up and went and
        grasped the horns of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Solomon was told, \u201CLook, Adonijah is afraid of King Solomon,
        and he has grasped the horns of the altar, saying, \u2018Let King Solomon
        swear to me first that he will surely not kill his servant with the sword!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Solomon said, \u201CIf he is a son of noble character, not a hair
        of his head will fall to the ground, but if evil is found in him, then he
        will die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Then King Solomon sent and brought him down from upon the altar.
        He came and did obeisance to King Solomon. Solomon said to him, \u201CGo
        to your house.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Instructions for Solomon"
      title: "David\u2019s Instructions for Solomon"
      number: 1
      content: 'The days of David came near for him to die, and he charged Solomon
        his son, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI am about to go the way of all the world. Be strong and be
        courageous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall keep the charge of Yahweh your God, to walk in his ways,
        to keep his statutes, his commandments, his judgments, and his testimonies,
        as are written in the law of Moses, so that you may prosper in all that you
        do and everywhere you turn, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "so that Yahweh may establish his word which he spoke concerning me,
        saying, \u2018If your sons take heed of their way, to walk before me in faithfulness,
        with all their heart and with all their soul, no man of yours will be cut
        off from the throne of Israel.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CMoreover, you also know what Joab the son of Zeruiah did to
        me when he dealt with the two commanders of the armies of Israel, to Abner
        son of Ner and to Amasa son of Jether, and he murdered them and put the blood
        of war in a time of peace. He put the blood of war on the leather belt that
        was on his waist and on the sandals which were on his feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You must act according to your wisdom, but you must not let his gray
        hair go down to Sheol in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Regarding the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, you shall do loyal
        love and let them be among those who eat at your table, because they met
        me when I fled from Absalom your brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And look, Shimei the son of Gera the son of the Benjaminite from
        Bahurim is with you. Now he cursed me severely when I went to Mahanaim, but
        he came down to meet me at the Jordan, so I swore to him by Yahweh, \u2018I
        surely will not kill you with the sword.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So then, do not leave him unpunished, for you are a wise man, and
        you will know what you must do to him. You must bring his grey hair down
        to Sheol with blood.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then David slept with his ancestors and was buried in the city of
        David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The days that David reigned over Israel were forty years; he reigned
        seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Adonijah\u2019s Persistence"
      title: "Adonijah\u2019s Persistence"
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Solomon sat on the throne of David his father, and his kingdom
        was firmly established. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon,
        and she said, \u201CAre you coming in peace?\u201D He said, \u201CPeace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CMay I have a word with you?\u201D Then she said,
        \u201CGo on.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said, \u201CYou know that the kingship was mine and that all Israel
        had set their face toward me as king, but the kingship turned around and
        became my brother\u2019s, for it was from Yahweh for him to have it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now one request I am asking from you, and you must not refuse me.\u201D
        Then she said to him, \u201CGo on.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said, \u201CPlease speak to King Solomon, for he will not refuse
        you, so that he will give to me Abishag the Shunnamite as wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Solomon\u2019s Responses to Adonijah, Joab, and Shimei"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Responses to Adonijah, Joab, and Shimei"
      number: 18
      content: "Then Bathsheba said, \u201CVery well, I will speak to the king concerning
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Bathsheba came to King Solomon to speak to him concerning Adonijah,
        and the king got up to meet her, bowed down to her, and then sat on his throne.
        Then he set up a throne for the king\u2019s mother, and she sat on his right. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "She said, \u201CI have one small request I am asking from you. Do
        not refuse me.\u201D The king said to her, \u201CAsk, my mother, for I will
        not refuse you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then she said, \u201CLet Abishag the Shunnamite be given to Adonijah
        your brother as wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "King Solomon answered and said to his mother, \u201CWhy are you asking
        Abishag the Shunnamite for Adonijah? Ask for him also the kingdom, for he
        is my brother, older than I; and ask for him also Abiathar the priest, and
        for Joab the son of Zeruiah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then King Solomon swore by Yahweh, saying, \u201CThus may God do
        to me and thus may he add, if Adonijah hasn\u2019t spoken this thing at the
        expense of his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So then, as Yahweh lives, who has established me and seated me on
        the throne of my father David and who has established for me a dynasty as
        he promised, then surely Adonijah will be put to death today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'King Solomon sent through the hand of Benaiah the son of Jehoiada,
        so he struck him, and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "To Abiathar the priest, the king said, \u201CGo to Anathoth, to your
        field, for you deserve to die, but on this day I will not kill you, for you
        carried the ark of the Lord Yahweh before David my father, and because you
        endured hardship in all the hardship that my father endured.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Solomon banished Abiathar from being priest to Yahweh, thus fulfilling
        the word which Yahweh had spoken concerning the house of Eli in Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When the message came to Joab (now Joab had supported Adonijah but
        had not supported Absalom), he fled to the tent of Yahweh and grasped the
        horns of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It was told to King Solomon that Joab had fled to the tent of Yahweh
        and was beside the altar. So Solomon sent word to Benaiah son of Jehoiada,
        saying, \u201CGo and fall upon him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Benaiah went to the tent of Yahweh, and he said to him, \u201CThus
        says the king: \u2018Come out.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D And he said, \u201CNo, for
        I want to die here.\u201D So Benaiah returned a word to the king, saying,
        \u201CThus Joab spoke, and thus he answered me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then the king said to him, \u201CDo as he spoke; fall upon him and
        bury him, and so you shall remove the innocent blood that Joab shed from
        on me and from on the house of my father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Yahweh will return his blood on his head, because he fell upon two
        men, more righteous and better than he, and he killed them with the sword,
        even though my father did not know it; namely Abner son of Ner, commander
        of the army of Israel, and Amasa son of Jether, commander of the army of
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And their blood will return on the head of Joab and on the head of
        his descendants forever, but for David and his descendants and for his house
        and his throne, there will be peace forever from Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Benaiah son of Jehoiada went up, and he fell on him and killed
        him, and he was buried in his house in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then the king appointed Benaiah the son of Jehoiada in his place
        over the army, and the king appointed Zadok the priest in place of Abiathar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then the king sent and summoned Shimei, and he said to him, \u201CBuild
        yourself a house in Jerusalem and live there, but you must not go out anywhere
        whatsoever from there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "It shall happen that on the day you go out and cross over the Wadi
        Kidron, know for certain that you will surely die. Your blood will be on
        your head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Shimei said to the king, \u201CThe word is good that my lord the
        king has spoken to me; thus will your servant do.\u201D So Shimei lived in
        Jerusalem many days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "It happened that at the end of three years, two of Shimei\u2019s
        slaves fled to Achish, son of Maacah, the king of Gath. They told Shimei,
        saying, \u201CYour slaves are here in Gath.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So Shimei got up and saddled his donkey, and he went to Gath, to
        Achish, to search for his slaves. So Shimei went and brought his slaves from
        Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'When Solomon was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath
        and had returned, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "the king sent and summoned Shimei, and he said to him, \u201CDid
        I not make you swear by Yahweh? I warned you, saying, \u2018On the day you
        go out and you go anywhere whatsoever, know for certain that you will surely
        die.\u2019 And you said to me, \u2018The word is good; I accept.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Why have you not kept the oath of Yahweh and the command which I
        commanded you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Then the king said to Shimei, \u201CYou know all the evil which your
        heart knows, what you did to David my father. Now Yahweh will return the
        evil on your head, "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "but King Solomon will be blessed and the throne of David will be
        established before Yahweh forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Then the king commanded Benaiah son of Jehoiada, and he went out
        and fell upon him, and he died. So the kingdom was established in the hand
        of Solomon. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Walk with Yahweh"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Walk with Yahweh"
      number: 1
      content: 'Solomon intermarried with Pharaoh the king of Egypt, and he took
        the daughter of Pharaoh and brought her to the city of David until he finished
        building his house, the house of Yahweh, and the walls of Jerusalem all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But the people were sacrificing on the high places, for the house
        for the name of Yahweh had not yet been built in those days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Solomon loved Yahweh, by walking in the statutes of David his father;
        only he was sacrificing and offering incense on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Solomon\u2019s Request for Wisdom"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Request for Wisdom"
      number: 4
      content: 'So the king went to Gibeon to sacrifice, for the great high place
        was there. Solomon used to offer a thousand burnt offerings on that altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Yahweh appeared to Solomon at Gibeon in a dream at night, and God
        said, \u201CAsk what I should give to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Solomon said, \u201CYou have shown great loyal love with your
        servant David my father, as he walked before you in faithfulness and in righteousness
        and in uprightness of heart with you. You have shown for him this great loyal
        love, and you have given a son to him who is sitting on his throne as it
        is this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So then, O Yahweh, you are my God. You have made your servant king
        in place of David my father though I am a young boy. I do not know going
        out or coming in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Your servant is in the middle of your people whom you have chosen;
        a great people who cannot be counted or numbered because of abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Give to your servant a listening heart to judge your people, to discern
        between good and bad, because who is able to judge this, your difficult people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The word was good in the eyes of the Lord that Solomon had asked
        this thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And God said to him, \u201CBecause you have asked this thing and
        you did not ask for yourself a long life and you did not ask riches for yourself
        and you did not ask for the life of your enemies, but you have asked for
        yourself the ability to make wise judgments;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'behold, I do hereby do according to your word. I hereby give you
        a wise and discerning heart; there was no one like you before you, nor afterwards
        will one like you arise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Too, what you have not asked I give to you: both riches and honor,
        so that no man among the kings will be like you all of your days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "If you will walk in my ways by keeping my statutes and my commandments,
        as David your father walked, then I will lengthen your days.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Solomon\u2019s Wisdom Tested: The Two Prostitutes"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wisdom Tested: The Two Prostitutes"
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Solomon awoke, and look, it was a dream, and he came to Jerusalem
        and stood before the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and he offered burnt
        offerings and presented fellowship offerings, and he held a feast for all
        of his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then two prostitutes came to the king, and they stood before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The one woman said, \u201CPlease my lord, I and this woman are living
        in one house, and I gave birth, with her in the house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It happened on the third day after my giving birth, this woman also
        gave birth, and we were together. There was not anyone with us in the house,
        only the two of us were in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the son of this woman died in the night because she laid on
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So she got up in the middle of the night, and she took my son from
        beside me while your servant was asleep, and she put him in her lap, and
        she put her dead son in my lap. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When I got up in the morning to nurse my son, behold, he was dead!
        When I looked closely at him in the morning, behold, it was not my son whom
        I had borne.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the other woman said, \u201CNo, for my son is the living one,
        and your son is the dead one.\u201D The other kept on saying, \u201CNo, for
        your son is the dead one, and my son is the living one,\u201D and so they
        argued in front of the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CThis one is saying, \u2018This is my son,
        the living one, but your son is the dead one,\u2019 and the other one keeps
        saying, \u2018But no! Your son is the dead one, and my son is living!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the king said, \u201CBring me a sword,\u201D and they brought
        the sword before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CDivide the living child into two, and give
        half to the one and half to the other.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the woman whose son was the living one spoke to the king because
        her compassion was aroused for her son, and she said, \u201CPlease, my lord,
        give her the living child, but certainly do not kill him!\u201D The other
        one was saying, \u201CAs for me, so for you! Divide him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king answered and said, \u201CGive the living child to her,
        and do not kill him; she is his mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When all of Israel heard the judgment that the king had rendered,
        they stood in awe of the king, because they realized that the wisdom of God
        was in him to execute justice. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Political Administration"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Political Administration"
      number: 1
      content: 'King Solomon was king over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now these are the officials who were his: Azariah the son of Zadok
        was the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elihoreph and Ahijah, the sons of Shisha, were the secretaries; Jehoshaphat
        the son of Ahilud was the recorder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the army, and Zadok and Abiathar
        were priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Azariah the son of Nathan was over the governors, and Zabud the son
        of Nathan was a priest, an advisor to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ahishar was over the palace, and Adoniram the son of Abda was over
        the forced labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Solomon had twelve governors over all Israel, and they sustained
        the king and his palace, each one was to sustain for each month of the year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'These are their names: Ben-Hur was in the hill country of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ben-Deker was in Makaz and in Shaalbim and in Beth-Shemesh and Elon
        of Beth-Hanan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ben-Hesed was in the Arubbot; Socoh and all the land of Hepher were
        his. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ben-Abinadab was in all of Naphat of Dor; Taphath the daughter of
        Solomon was his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Baanah the son of Ahilud was in Taanach and Megiddo and all Beth-Shean
        which is beside Zarethan below Jezreel, of Beth-Shean up to Abel-Meholah
        up to the other side of Jokmeam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ben-Geber was in Ramoth-Gilead; the villages of Jair, the son of
        Manasseh which are in the Gilead were his, and the region of Argob which
        is in the Bashan, sixty great cities, with walls having crossbars of bronze,
        were his. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ahinadab the son of Iddo was in Mahanaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ahimaaz was in Naphtali; he moreover also had taken Basemath the
        daughter of Solomon as wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Baanah the son of Hushai was in Asher and Bealoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah was in Issachar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Shimei the son of Ela was in Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Geber the son of Uri was in the land of Gilead, the land of Sihon,
        the king of the Amorites, and of Og, the king of Bashan; one governor which
        was over the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Prosperity"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Prosperity"
      number: 20
      content: 'Judah and Israel were as many as the sand which is on the seashore
        in abundance, eating and drinking and rejoicing! '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: ' Now Solomon was ruling over all the kingdoms from the River to the
        land of the Philistines, and up to the border of Egypt, who were bringing
        tribute and were serving Solomon all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The food of Solomon for one day was thirty dry measures of choice
        meal and sixty dry measures of flour; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'ten stall-fed oxen and twenty pasture-fed oxen and a hundred sheep,
        besides deer and buck gazelles and roebucks and well-fed fowls. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For he was ruling over all the west of the River from Tiphsah up
        to Gaza, over all the kings west of the River; and he had peace from every
        side all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Judah and Israel lived in security, each man under his vine and under
        his fig tree, from Dan as far as Beersheba, all the days of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Solomon had forty thousand stalls of horses for his war chariots
        and twelve thousand horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'These governors sustained King Solomon and all who came near to the
        table of King Solomon, each in his month; they did not omit anything. '
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Literature, Zoology, Biology, Dendrology"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Literature, Zoology, Biology, Dendrology"
      number: 28
      content: 'The barley and the straw for the horses and for packhorses they brought
        to the place where they were, each according to his share. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'God gave wisdom to Solomon and very great discernment, as well as
        breadth of understanding, as the sand which is on the edge of the seashore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The wisdom of Solomon was greater than the wisdom of all the people
        of the east and more than all the wisdom of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He was wiser than all the men: Ethan the Ezrahite; Heman, Calcol,
        and Darda the children of Mahol; and he was very well known.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He spoke three thousand proverbs, and his songs were one thousand
        and five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He spoke concerning the trees, from the cedar which is in Lebanon
        up to the hyssop which grows on the wall; he also spoke concerning the animals,
        concerning the birds, concerning the creeping things, and concerning the
        fish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'They came from all the nations to hear the wisdom of Solomon; from
        all the kings of the earth who had heard of his wisdom. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Architecture"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wisdom: Architecture"
      number: 1
      content: 'Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Solomon when he heard that
        they had anointed him as king in place of his father, for Hiram had always
        been a friend for David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Solomon sent to Hiram, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou knew David my father, that he was not able to build a house
        for the name of Yahweh his God, in view of the warfare which surrounded him,
        until Yahweh placed them under the soles of his feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But now Yahweh my God has given me rest all around me. There is no
        adversary, and there is no bad occurrence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Here I am, intending to build a house for the name of Yahweh my God,
        as Yahweh promised to my father David, saying, \u2018Your son, whom I will
        set in your place on your throne, shall build the house for my name.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So then, command that they may cut cedars for me from Lebanon, and
        let my servants be with your servants. The wage of your servants I will give
        to you according to all that you say, for you know that there is no one among
        us who knows how to cut timber like the Sidonians.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When Hiram heard the words of Solomon, he rejoiced greatly, and he
        said, \u201CBlessed be Yahweh this day, who has given to David a wise son
        over this great people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hiram sent to Solomon, saying, \u201CI have heard what you have sent
        to me; I will do all of your desire concerning the timber of cedars and concerning
        the timber of cypresses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "My servants will bring them down from Lebanon to the sea, and I will
        make them into rafts in the sea to float to the place which you indicated
        to me. Then I shall break them up there, and you may carry them further,
        and you shall meet my needs by giving food for my house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Hiram was giving to Solomon the cedar timbers and the cypress
        timbers, everything he needed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Solomon gave to Hiram twenty thousand dry measures of wheat
        as food for his household, and twenty dry measures of specially prepared
        olive oil; thus Solomon gave to Hiram year by year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yahweh gave wisdom to Solomon as he promised to him, and there was
        peace between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made a covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then King Solomon conscripted a forced labor from all Israel, and
        the forced labor numbered thirty thousand men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He sent them to Lebanon, ten thousand every month; the work groups
        were a month in Lebanon and two months at home; now Adoniram was over the
        forced labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Solomon had seventy thousand common laborers and eighty thousand
        stone craftsmen in the hill country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Besides the chiefs of the officers Solomon had, there were three
        thousand three hundred having charge over the people who were doing the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When the king commanded, they quarried great stones and precious
        stones to lay the foundation of the house with hewn stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Solomon\u2019s builders and Hiram\u2019s builders and the Gebalites
        hewed stones, and they prepared the timber and the stone to build the house. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Builds the Temple for Yahweh'
      title: Solomon Builds the Temple for Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: "It happened in the four hundred and eightieth year after the Israelites
        went out from the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon\u2019s rule
        over Israel, the month of Ziv (that is the second month), that he began to
        build the house for Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the house that King Solomon built for Yahweh was sixty cubits
        in its length and twenty cubits in its width and thirty cubits in its height. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The vestibule on the face of the main hall of the temple was twenty
        cubits in its length, and the width of the temple was ten cubits wide on
        the face of the temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he made for the temple specially designed framed windows, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and he built a structure against the wall of the temple running all
        along the walls of the house, for the outer sanctuary and for the inner sanctuary,
        and made side rooms all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The lower structure was five cubits in its width and the middle was
        six cubits in its width and the third was seven cubits in its width, for
        he made niches for the temple all around to the outside, so that beams would
        not attach to the walls of the temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now while the temple was being built, it was built with stones finished
        at the quarry, so that no hammer or stone shaping tool or any instrument
        of iron was heard in the temple as it was being built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The doorway of the side room in the middle of the side of the temple
        was on the south; they went up with a stairway to the middle and from the
        middle to the third floor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So he built the house and finished it. He covered the temple with
        rafters and wood planks and with the cedars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He also built the structure against all of the temple five cubits
        in height and fastened it to the temple with beams of cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the word of Yahweh came to Solomon, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CRegarding this temple that you are building: if you walk in
        my ordinances and if you do my judgments and you keep all my commandments
        to walk in them, then I will establish my promise with you which I made to
        David your father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And I will dwell among the Israelites, and I will not forsake my
        people Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Solomon built the temple and finished it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He lined the walls of the inside of the house with boards of cedar;
        from the floor of the temple up to the rafters of the ceiling he covered
        them with wood on the inside. He also covered the floor of the temple with
        cypress boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He built twenty cubits from the rear of the house with boards of
        cedar from the floor up to the ceiling, and he built for it an inner sanctuary
        on the inside, as the most holy place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The main hall of the temple was forty cubits in front of the inner
        sanctuary,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'with the cedar within the inner house having carvings of gourds and
        buds of flowers. It was entirely of cedar; there was not a stone visible. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now in the inner sanctuary in the middle of the temple he prepared
        the inside to place the ark of the covenant of Yahweh there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In front, the inner sanctuary was twenty cubits long and twenty cubits
        wide and twenty cubits high, and he overlaid it with pure gold and covered
        the altar with cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Solomon overlaid the temple on the inside with pure gold, and he
        drew across it with golden chains in front of the inner sanctuary, which
        he overlaid with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All of the temple he overlaid with gold until all of the temple was
        finished; all of the altar which belonged to the inner sanctuary he overlaid
        with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He made two cherubim of olive wood for the inner sanctuary, ten cubits
        high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Five cubits was the first wing of the cherub, and five cubits the
        second wing of the cherub, from the tip of his one wing up to the tip of
        his other wing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The second cherub was ten cubits according to the same measurement,
        and there was one shape for the two cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The height of the first cherub was ten cubits and so was the second
        cherub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He placed the cherubim in the middle of the inner house, and they
        spread out the wings of the cherubim; the wing of the first cherub touched
        against the wall and the wing of the second cherub was touching against the
        second wall; their wings spread to the middle of the house and were touching
        wing to wing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He also overlaid the cherubim with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'On all of the walls around the house, he carved engravings of cherubim
        and palm tree images and budding flowers both inside and out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He overlaid the floor of the house with gold both inside and out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He made doors of olive wood for the doorway of the inner sanctuary,
        as well as for the doorpost of the fifth doorframe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'On the two doors of olive wood he made carvings of cherubim and palm
        tree images and budding flowers, and he overlaid them with gold by beating
        out the gold on the cherubim and the palm tree images. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Thus he made doorframes of olive wood on four sides for the doorway
        of the main hall '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'and two doors of cypress wood; one door with two folding panels and
        the second door with two folding panels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'He carved cherubim and palm tree images and budding flowers and overlaid
        them with gold evenly applied on the carved work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then he built the inner courtyard with three rows of dressed stone
        and a row of cedar beams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'In the fourth year, the house of Yahweh was founded in the month
        of Ziv. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'In the eleventh year in the month of Bul, that is, the eighth month,
        the house was finished according to all his specifications and according
        to all his plans. He had built it in seven years. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Continues to Build'
      title: Solomon Continues to Build
      number: 1
      content: 'Solomon built his house over thirteen years, and he finished all
        of his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He built the House of the Forest of Lebanon; one hundred cubits its
        length, fifty cubits its width, and thirty cubits its height, on four rows
        of cedar pillars and cedar beams atop the pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It was covered with cedar above, and the supporting beams which were
        on the forty-five pillars, fifteen to the row. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'There were three rows of specially designed windows; with window
        to window three times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All of the doorways and the doorframes had four-sided casings, with
        opening to opposite opening three times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The hall of pillars he made fifty cubits in its length and thirty
        cubits in its width, and a porch was in front of them, with pillars and an
        overhang in front of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He made the hall of the throne where he would pronounce judgment,
        the hall of justice, and it was covered with cedar from the floor to the
        rafters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'His house where he would live in the next courtyard on the inside
        of the porch was like this work, and he would make a house like this porch
        for the daughter of Pharaoh whom Solomon had taken as wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All of these were of precious stones, according to the measurement
        of dressed stone, sawn with a saw on all sides; from the foundation up to
        the eaves and from the outside up to the great courtyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The foundation was of precious stones, and large stones of ten cubits
        and stones of eight cubits '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'with precious stones above, just the right size, and cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The great courtyard all around had three rows of dressed stones and
        a row of cedar beams; for both the courtyard of the inner house of Yahweh
        and for the porch of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'King Solomon invited and received Hiram from Tyre. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He was the son of a widow woman from the tribe of Naphtali, and his
        father was a man of Tyre, an artisan of bronze. He was filled with wisdom
        and with ability and with the knowledge to do all the work with the bronze.
        And he came to King Solomon, and he did all of his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He cast the two pillars out of bronze; eighteen cubits was the height
        of the first, and a cord of twelve cubits would encircle the second pillar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He made two capitals to place on the tops of the pillars out of molten
        bronze; the first capital was five cubits in height, and the second capital
        was five cubits in height. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A network of latticework and wreaths of chainwork with small chains
        were for the capitals which were on top of the pillars; seven for the first
        capital and seven for the second capital. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He also made the pillars with two rows around on the lattice, each
        to cover the capitals which were on top, out of the pomegranate-shaped ornaments,
        and thus he did for the second capital as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And on the capitals which were on top of the pillars in the porch
        were works of lilies four cubits high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And capitals were on the two pillars above near the bulging section
        which was beside the lattice, and two hundred pomegranate-shaped ornaments
        were in rows all around on the second capital. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He set up the pillars for the porch of the main hall; he erected
        the pillar on the right and called its name Jakin, and he set up the pillar
        on the left and called its name Boaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'On the top of the pillars was a work of lilies; and so the work of
        the pillars was finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He also made the molten sea, ten cubits in diameter, and five cubits
        was its height. A measuring line of thirty cubits would encircle it all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Gourds were under its rim surrounding it all around; ten to the cubit,
        surrounding the sea all around with two rows of gourds, which were cast when
        he cast the metal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sea was standing on twelve oxen, with three facing to the north,
        three facing to the west, three facing to the south, and three facing to
        the east. The sea was on top of them, with all of their hindquarters turned
        to the inside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Its thickness was a handbreadth, but its rim was as the work on the
        brim of a cup, like the bud of a lily; it held two thousand baths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He made the ten stands of bronze; each stand was four cubits long,
        four cubits wide, and three cubits in height. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now this was the construction of the stands: there were frames for
        them and frames between the crossbars, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and on the frames which were between the crossbars were lions, oxen,
        and cherubim. On the crossbars both above and beneath the lions and oxen
        were works of cascading wreaths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There were four bronze wheels for each of the stands, with bronze
        axles; the four support pedestals for these were under the basin, and the
        supports were decorated on each side with wreaths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Its opening from the inside of the capital and above was a cubit;
        its pedestal was a round work of a cubit and a half; moreover, on its opening
        were the carvings with four-sided frames, not circular. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Four of the wheels were underneath the frames, and the axles of the
        wheels were on the stands. The height of each wheel was a cubit and a half. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The construction of the wheel was like the construction of the wheel
        of the chariot; their axles, their rims, their spokes, and their naves were
        all cast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The four supports were the four corners of each stand, with the stand
        supporting it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'On top of the stand was half a cubit deep, circular all around, and
        on the top of the stand were its supports and its frames. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'He engraved on the plates, on its supports, and on its frame cherubim,
        lions and images of a palm tree, according to the space for each, with wreaths
        all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He made the ten stands like this in one cast, with the same measurement
        and shape for each of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'He also made ten bronze basins, each holding forty baths; each basin
        was four cubits, one basin on each of the ten stands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'He placed five of the stands on the south side of the house and five
        on the north side of the house, and the sea he set on the southeast side
        of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Hiram also made the basins and the shovels and the bowls for drinking
        wine; and so Hiram finished doing all of the work that he was to do for King
        Solomon in the house of Yahweh: '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'the two pillars and the bowls of the capitals which were atop the
        two pillars, and the two lattice works to cover the two bowls of the capitals
        which were atop the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'and the four hundred pomegranate-shaped ornaments for the two lattice
        works, the two rows of pomegranate-shaped ornaments for each latticework
        to cover the two bowls of the capitals which were on the surface of the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'and the ten stands and the ten basins on the stands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'and the one sea and the twelve oxen under the sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'and the pots, the shovels, and the bowls for drinking wine. All the
        vessels of the tent which Hiram had made for King Solomon for the house of
        Yahweh were polished bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The king had cast them in the plain of the Jordan with the casting
        mold set in the ground between Succoth and Zarethan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Solomon left all of the vessels unweighed because of their very great
        abundance, so the weight of the bronze could not be determined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Solomon also made all of the vessels which were in the house of Yahweh:
        the golden altar and the golden table on which was the bread of the presence; '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'as well as the five lampstands of beaten gold at the south and five
        lampstands at the north before the presence of the inner sanctuary, with
        the flower-shaped ornaments, the lamps, and the pair of tongs all of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'The cups, the snuffers, the bowls for drinking wine, the bowls for
        the incense, and the firepans were made from beaten gold; the facades for
        the doors of the inner house, for the most holy place, for the doors of the
        main hall of the temple were of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'When all of the work which king Solomon did on the house of Yahweh
        was completed, Solomon brought out the holy objects of his father David,
        the silver and the gold and the vessels, which he put in the treasury rooms
        of the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Dedication of the Temple'
      title: The Dedication of the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'At that time, Solomon assembled the elders of Israel, all the heads
        of the tribes, and the leaders of the families of the Israelites before King
        Solomon, in order to bring up the ark of the covenant of Yahweh from the
        city of David, that is, Zion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'All the men of Israel assembled before King Solomon at the festival
        in the month of Ethnaim, that is, the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All the elders of Israel came, and the priests carried the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they brought up the ark of Yahweh and the tent of assembly and
        all of the holy vessels that were in the tent; the priests and the Levites
        brought them up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'King Solomon and all the assembly of Israel who were assembling with
        him in the presence of the ark were sacrificing sheep and oxen that could
        not be counted nor numbered because of abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The priests brought the ark of the covenant of Yahweh to its place
        in the inner sanctuary of the house, to the most holy place, under the wings
        of the cherubim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'for the cherubim were spreading their wings over the place of the
        ark. The cherubim overshadowed the ark and its poles from above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The poles were long, and the ends of the poles could be seen from
        the holy place in front of the inner sanctuary, but they could not be seen
        from the outside, and they are there until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'There was not anything in the ark except the two tablets of stone
        which Moses had placed there at Horeb, where Yahweh made a covenant with
        the Israelites after they went out from the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When the priests went out from the holy place, the cloud filled the
        house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Solomon\u2019s Proclamation to the Assembly of Israel"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Proclamation to the Assembly of Israel"
      number: 11
      content: 'The priests were not able to stand to minister because of the presence
        of the cloud, for the glory of Yahweh filled the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Solomon said, \u201CYahweh has said that he would dwell in the
        very thick cloud. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I have certainly built a lofty house for you, a place for you to
        live forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the king turned his face around, and he blessed all of the assembly
        of Israel. (Now all the assembly of Israel was standing). '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBlessed be Yahweh the God of Israel who has promised
        with his mouth to David my father and fulfilled by his oath, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018From the day that I brought out my people Israel from Egypt
        I have not chosen a city from all the tribes of Israel to build a house where
        my name might be, but I have chosen David to be over my people Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'David my father desired to build a house for the name of Yahweh the
        God of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "but Yahweh said to David my father, \u2018Because you desired to
        build a house for my name, you did well in that it was within your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "However, you will not build the house, but your son who has come
        from your loins, he shall build the house for my name.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Yahweh has carried out his promise which he had made; I have risen
        in place of David my father, and I sit on the throne of Israel as Yahweh
        promised, and I have built the house for the name of Yahweh the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Solomon\u2019s Prayer to Yahweh"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Prayer to Yahweh"
      number: 21
      content: "I have provided a place there for the ark, in which is the covenant
        which Yahweh made with our ancestors when He brought them out of the land
        of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Solomon stood before the altar of Yahweh in the presence of
        all of the assembly of Israel, and he spread out his hands to the heavens, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and he said, \u201CO Yahweh, God of Israel, there is no god like
        you in the heavens above or on the earth beneath, keeping the covenant and
        the loyal love for your servants who are walking before you with all their
        heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have kept for your servant David my father what you promised
        to him, and you have spoken with your mouth, and with your hand you have
        fulfilled it this very day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So then, O Yahweh, God of Israel, keep for your servant David my
        father what you promised to him, saying, \u2018For you, no man will be cut
        off from before me who will be sitting on the throne of Israel, if only your
        sons keep their ways to walk before me just as you have walked before me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So then, O God of Israel, please let your word be confirmed which
        you have promised to your servant David my father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For will God really dwell on the earth? Behold, the heavens and the
        heaven of heavens could not contain you! How could this house that I have
        built? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You must regard the prayer of your servant and his plea! O Yahweh
        my God, listen to the pleading and to the prayer that your servant is praying
        before you this day, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "so that your eyes will be open to this house night and day, to the
        place which you said, \u2018My name will be there,\u2019 to hear the prayer
        that your servant prays toward this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You must listen to the plea of your servant and your people Israel
        which they pray toward this place; and you must hear from the place where
        you live, from heaven you must hear and you must forgive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'If a man sins against his neighbor and he pronounces an oath against
        him to curse him, and the curse comes before your altar in this house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'then you shall hear in heaven and you shall act and you shall judge
        your servant, to declare the wicked guilty by bringing his way upon his head
        and to declare the righteous innocent by rewarding him according to his righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When your people Israel are defeated before the enemy because they
        sinned against you, and when they turn to you and confess your name and pray
        and beg for mercy from you in this house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'then you shall hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your people
        Israel, and you shall bring them back to the ground which you gave to their
        ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'When you shut up the heavens so there is no rain because they have
        sinned against you, then they pray to this place and they confess your name
        and they return from their sin because you punished them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'then you shall hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your servants
        and your people Israel, for you will teach them the good way in which they
        should go, and you will give rain upon your land which you have given to
        your people as an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'If there should be in the land famine or disease, if there should
        be blight or mildew or locust or caterpillars, if it happens that his enemy
        lays siege against him in the land of his gates, if any plague or any disease, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'any prayer or any plea which is offered by any person for all of
        your people Israel, who each knows the infestation of his own heart and spreads
        out his palms to this house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then you shall hear in heaven the place of your dwelling, and you
        shall forgive and act and give to the man whose heart you know, according
        to all his ways, for you alone know the heart of all the sons of man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Do these things so that they may fear you all the days that they
        live on the face of the land that you gave to our ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Also for the foreigner who is not from your people Israel, and he
        comes from a distant land because of your name, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '(for they shall hear of your great name and your powerful hand and
        your outstretched arm), and he shall come and pray toward this house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'you shall hear in heaven, the place of your dwelling, and act according
        to all that the foreigner calls to you, so that all the peoples of the earth
        may know your name, to fear you as your people Israel, and to know that your
        name has been invoked over this house that I have built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'If your people go out to battle against his enemy in the way that
        you shall send them and they pray to Yahweh, toward the city which you have
        chosen and the house which I have built for your name, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'then you shall hear in heaven their prayer and their plea, and you
        shall vindicate them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CIf they sin against you (for there is not a person who does
        not sin) and you are angry with them and you give them to an enemy and they
        take them captive to the land of the enemy far or near, "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "and then they return their heart in the land where they have been
        taken captive and they return and plead to you in the land of their captivity,
        saying, \u2018We have sinned and we did wrong. We acted wickedly,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'if they return to you with all of their heart and with all of their
        soul in the land of their enemies who took them captive and they pray to
        you toward their land which you gave to their ancestors, the city that you
        have chosen and the house that you built for your name, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'then you shall hear in heaven, the place of your dwelling, their
        prayer and their plea, and you shall vindicate them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'You shall forgive your people who sinned against you, even for all
        their transgressions which they committed against you. You shall give them
        compassion before their captors so that they may have compassion on them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'for they are your people and your inheritance whom you brought from
        Egypt from the middle of the smelter of iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'O, that your eyes may be open to the plea of your servant and to
        the plea of your people Israel, to listen to them in all things when they
        call to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: Solomon Charges the People Israel'
      title: Solomon Charges the People Israel
      number: 53
      content: "For you have separated them for yourself as an inheritance from all
        the peoples of the earth, as you promised through the hand of Moses your
        servant when you brought out our ancestors from Egypt, my Lord Yahweh!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'It happened that when Solomon finished praying to Yahweh all of the
        prayer and this plea, he got up from before the altar of Yahweh, from kneeling
        down on his knees with his palms outstretched to heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'He stood and blessed all of the assembly of Israel with a loud voice,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "\u201CBlessed be Yahweh who gave a resting place to his people Israel.
        According to all that he promised, not one word has fallen from all of his
        promises concerning the good which he spoke through the hand of Moses his
        servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'May Yahweh our God be with us as he was with our ancestors, and may
        he not leave us or abandon us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'to incline our hearts toward him, to walk in all his ways and to
        keep his commandments, his statutes, and his judgments which he commanded
        our ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Let these my words which I pleaded before Yahweh be near to Yahweh
        our God, by day and by night, to maintain the justice of his servant and
        the justice of his people Israel as each day requires  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'so that all of the people of the earth may know that Yahweh, he is
        God; there is none other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: The Great Confirming Sacrifice'
      title: The Great Confirming Sacrifice
      number: 61
      content: "Let your heart be completely with Yahweh our God by walking in his
        statutes, by keeping his commands as this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Then the king and all of Israel with him offered a sacrifice in the
        presence of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Solomon sacrificed the fellowship offerings which he offered to Yahweh:
        twenty-two thousand oxen and one hundred and twenty thousand sheep; and the
        king and all of the Israelites dedicated the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'On that day the king consecrated the middle of the courtyard before
        the house of Yahweh because he offered there the burnt offerings, the grain
        offerings, and the fat of the fellowship offerings because the bronze altar
        that was in the presence of Yahweh was too small to hold the burnt offerings
        and the grain offerings and the fat of the fellowship offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'Solomon held the festival at that time and all of Israel with him,
        a great assembly from Lebo Hamath up to the wadi of Egypt before Yahweh our
        God, for seven days and seven days, a total of fourteen days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'On the eighth day, he sent the people away, and they blessed the
        king, and they went to their tents rejoicing and in good spirits because
        of all the goodness that Yahweh had shown to David his servant and to Israel
        his people. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Challenge to Solomon"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Challenge to Solomon"
      number: 1
      content: "It happened that as Solomon finished the building of the house of
        Yahweh, the king\u2019s house, and all the things Solomon desired to do, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yahweh appeared to Solomon a second time, as he had appeared to him
        in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Yahweh said to him, \u201CI have heard your prayer and your plea
        which you have made before me. I have consecrated this house which you have
        built, by putting my name there forever. My eyes and my heart will always
        be there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As for you, if you walk before me as David your father walked, with
        integrity of heart and with uprightness, to do according to all that I have
        commanded you, and if you keep my ordinances and my judgments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "then I will establish the throne of your kingdom over Israel forever,
        as I promised David your father, saying, \u2018A man will not be cut off
        for you from upon the throne of Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf ever you or any of your descendants turn from following
        me and do not keep my commandments and my ordinances that I have set before
        you and you go and serve other gods and bow down to them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then I will cut Israel off from the face of the land that I have
        given to them, even the house which I have consecrated for my name I will
        cast away from my face; and Israel shall become a proverb and an object of
        taunting among all the peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "This house shall become a heap of ruins; all those passing by will
        be appalled by it and hiss, and they will say, \u2018On what account did
        Yahweh do this to this land and to this house?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Solomon and Hiram Complete Their Agreement'
      title: Solomon and Hiram Complete Their Agreement
      number: 9
      content: "And they will say, \u2018Because they have forsaken Yahweh their
        God who brought their ancestors out from the land of Egypt and they embraced
        other gods and bowed down to them and served them. Therefore, Yahweh brought
        on them all of this disaster.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'It happened at the end of twenty years in which Solomon had built
        the two houses, the house of Yahweh and the house of the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'since Hiram king of Tyre had supplied Solomon with wood of cedar
        and with wood of cypresses and with the gold according to all his desire,
        then King Solomon gave twenty cities in the land of the Galilee to Hiram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Hiram went out from Tyre to see the cities that Solomon had given
        him, but they were not right in his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So he said, \u201CWhat are these cities that you have given to me,
        my brother?\u201D So they are called the land of Cabul until this day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Solomon\u2019s Accomplishments"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Accomplishments"
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Hiram sent to the king a hundred and twenty talents of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This is the account of the forced labor that King Solomon conscripted
        to build the house of Yahweh and his house, the Millo, the walls of Jerusalem,
        Hazor, Megiddo, and Gezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Pharaoh, the king of Egypt, had gone up and captured Gezer and burnt
        it with fire. He had also killed the Canaanites who were living in the city
        and had given it as a dowry to his daughter, the wife of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Solomon rebuilt Gezer and Lower Beth-Horon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'as well as Baalath and Tamar in the wilderness in the land; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and he also built all of the storage cities which were Solomon\u2019s,
        the cities for the chariots, the cities for the cavalry, and all of Solomon\u2019s
        desire that he wanted to build in Jerusalem and in Lebanon and in all the
        land of his dominion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'All of the people who were remaining from the Amorites, the Hittites,
        the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites who were not of the Israelites,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'their children who remained after them in the land, whom the Israelites
        were not able to completely destroy, Solomon conscripted them for forced
        labor, until this very day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But from the Israelites Solomon did not make a slave, but they were
        the men of war, his officers, his commanders, his captains, and the commanders
        of his chariots and his cavalry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These were the commanders of the overseers who were over the work
        for Solomon, five hundred and fifty, ruling over the people doing the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'As soon as the daughter of Pharaoh went up from the city of David
        to her house which he built for her, then he built the Millo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Solomon sacrificed three times a year: burnt offerings and fellowship
        offerings on the altar that he had built to Yahweh, and he offered incense
        with it before Yahweh; and so he completed the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'King Solomon also built a fleet of ships at Ezion-Geber which is
        near Elath on the shore of the Red Sea in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hiram sent his servants with the fleet of ships, sailors who knew
        the sea, with the servants of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They went to Ophir and imported from there four hundred and twenty
        talents of gold, and they brought it to King Solomon. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Visit of the Queen of Sheba'
      title: The Visit of the Queen of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the queen of Sheba had heard of the fame of Solomon regarding
        the name of Yahweh, and she came to test him with hard questions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So she came to Jerusalem with very great wealth; with camels carrying
        spices, very much gold, and precious stones. She came to Solomon, and she
        spoke to him all that was on her heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Solomon answered all of her questions; there was not a thing hidden
        from the king which he could not explain to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the queen of Sheba observed all the wisdom of Solomon and the
        house which he had built, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the food of his table, the seat of his servants, the manner of his
        servants and their clothing, his cupbearers, and his burnt offerings which
        he offered in the house of Yahweh, she was breathless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then she said to the king, \u201CThe report which I heard in my land
        was true concerning your accomplishments and your wisdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I had not believed the report to be true until I came and my eyes
        had seen, and behold! The half had not been told to me. Your wisdom and prosperity
        surpass the report that I had heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Happy are your men and happy are these your servants who stand before
        you continually hearing your wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "May Yahweh your God be blessed, who has delighted in you to set you
        on the throne of Israel, because of the love of Yahweh for Israel forever,
        and he has made you king to execute justice and righteousness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then she gave the king a hundred and twenty talents of gold, abundant
        spices, and precious stones. Spices as these did not come again in such abundance
        as that which the queen of Sheba brought to King Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover, the fleet of ships of Hiram which carried the gold from
        Ophir also brought from Ophir abundant amounts of almug wood and precious
        stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The king made a raised structure for the house of Yahweh and for
        the house of the king out of the almug wood, as well as lyres and harps for
        the singers. This much almug wood has not come nor been seen again up to
        this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all of her desire that she
        asked, besides that which King Solomon freely offered her. Then she turned
        and went to her land with her servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The weight of the gold that came to Solomon in one year was six hundred
        and sixty-six talents of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'apart from that of the men of the traders and the profits of the
        traders, and all the kings of the Arabs and the governors of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'King Solomon made two hundred shields of hammered gold; six hundred
        measures of gold went up over each shield. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Also he made three hundred small shields of hammered gold; three
        minas of gold went up over each of the small shields; and the king put them
        into the House of the Forest of Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The king also made a large ivory throne, and he overlaid it with
        fine gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Six steps led up to the throne, and there was a circular top to the
        throne behind it, and armrests were on each side of the seat, with two lions
        standing beside the armrests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Twelve lions were standing there, six on each of the six steps on
        either side; nothing like this was made for any of the kingdoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'All of the drinking vessels of King Solomon were gold, and all the
        vessels for the House of the Forest of Lebanon were pure gold. There was
        no silver; it was not considered as something valuable in the days of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the fleet of Tarshish belonged to the king and was on the sea
        with the fleet of Hiram; once every three years the fleet of Tarshish used
        to come carrying gold and silver, ivory, apes, and baboons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'King Solomon was greater than all the kings of the earth with respect
        to wealth and wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All of the earth was seeking the presence of Solomon, to hear his
        wisdom which God had put in his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'They were each bringing his gift; objects of silver and objects of
        gold, clothing, weapons, spices, horses, and mules. This used to happen year
        after year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Solomon gathered chariots and horses; he had fourteen hundred chariots
        and twelve thousand horses. He stationed them in the cities of the chariots
        and with the king in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The king made the silver in Jerusalem as the stones, and the cedars
        he made as the sycamore fig trees which are in the Shephelah in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The import of the horses which were Solomon\u2019s was from Egypt
        and from Kue; the traders of the king received horses from Kue at a price. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A chariot went up and went out from Egypt at six hundred silver shekels
        and a horse at a hundred and fifty. So it was for all the kings of the Hittites
        and for the kings of Aram; by their hand they were exported. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Foreign Wives"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Foreign Wives"
      number: 1
      content: 'King Solomon loved many foreign women: the daughter of Pharaoh, Moabite,
        Ammonite, Edomite, Sidonian, Hittite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "from the nations which Yahweh had said to the Israelites, \u201CYou
        shall not marry them, and they shall not marry you. They will certainly turn
        your heart after other gods.\u201D But Solomon clung to them to love. "
      comments: []
    - name: "3: Solomon\u2019s Apostasy"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Apostasy"
      number: 3
      content: 'He had seven hundred princesses and three hundred concubines, and
        his wives turned his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It happened at the time of Solomon\u2019s old age that his wives
        guided his heart after other gods, and his heart was not fully with Yahweh
        his God as the heart of David his father had been. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Solomon went after Ashtoreth the god of the Sidonians and after Molech
        the abhorrence of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Solomon did evil in the eyes of Yahweh and did not fully follow
        after Yahweh as David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'At that time, Solomon built a high place for Chemosh, the abomination
        of Moab, on the mountain which faces Jerusalem and for Molech, the abomination
        of the Ammonites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Yahweh\u2019s Judgment on Solomon"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Judgment on Solomon"
      number: 8
      content: 'Thus he did for all of his foreign wives, offering incense and sacrificing
        to their gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yahweh was angry with Solomon, for he had turned his heart from Yahweh,
        the God of Israel who had appeared to him twice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he had commanded him concerning this matter not to go after other
        gods, but he did not keep that which Yahweh commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Yahweh said to Solomon, \u201CBecause this was with you, and you
        did not keep my covenant and my ordinances which I have commanded you, I
        will certainly tear the kingdom from you, and I will give it to your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'However, I will not do it in your days, for the sake of David your
        father; from the hand of your son I will tear it away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet all of the kingdom I will not tear away. I will give one tribe
        to your son for the sake of my servant David and for the sake of Jerusalem
        which I have chosen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Yahweh raised an adversary against Solomon, Hadad the Edomite,
        from the descendants of that king in Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'It had happened that when David was at Edom, Joab the commander of
        the army went up to bury the slain, and he killed every male in Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For Joab and all Israel had stayed there six months until he exterminated
        every male in Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But Hadad himself had fled, and some Edomite men from the servants
        of his father with him, to go to Egypt, when Hadad was a young boy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They had set out from Midian until they came to Paran where they
        took men from Paran with them and came to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt.
        He gave to him a house and assigned food for him and gave him land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hadad found great favor in the eyes of Pharaoh, and he gave him the
        sister of his wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen, as wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sister of Tahpenes bore Genubath his son for him, and Tahpenes
        weaned him in the middle of the house of Pharaoh. Genubath was in the house
        of Pharaoh in the midst of the children of Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now Hadad heard in Egypt that David had slept with his ancestors
        and that Joab the commander of the army was dead. Then Hadad said to Pharaoh,
        \u201CSend me away that I may go to my land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Pharaoh said to him, \u201CWhat do you lack with me that you now
        are seeking to go to your land?\u201D He said, \u201CNo, but you must surely
        send me away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'God had also raised Rezon the son of Eliada as an adversary against
        him, who had fled from Hadadezer the king of Zobah, his master. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He gathered men around him and he became the commander of bandits.
        When David killed some of them, they went to Damascus and settled there,
        and they reigned in Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Yahweh Raises Up Jeroboam'
      title: Yahweh Raises Up Jeroboam
      number: 25
      content: 'He was an adversary for Israel all the days of Solomon, and along
        with the evil that Hadad did, he detested Israel while he reigned over Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephraimite from Zeredah (now the
        name of his mother was Zeruah, a widow woman), a servant of Solomon rebelled
        against the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This is the reason that he rebelled against the king: when Solomon
        built the Millo, he closed the gap of the city of David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the man Jeroboam was a man of ability, and Solomon saw that the
        young man was a diligent worker, so he appointed him over all of the forced
        labor for the house of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'It happened at that time that Jeroboam went out from Jerusalem, and
        he accidentally met Ahijah the Shilonite the prophet on the way. Now he had
        clothed himself with new clothing. While the two of them were alone in the
        field, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Ahijah took hold of the new cloak which was on him and tore it into
        twelve pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he said to Jeroboam, \u201CTake for yourself ten pieces, for
        thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u2018Behold, I am about to tear the
        kingdom from the hand of Solomon, and I will give to you ten tribes, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'but one tribe shall be for him, for the sake of my servant David
        and for the sake of Jerusalem, the city which I have chosen from all the
        tribes of Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'because he has forsaken me, and they bowed down to Ashtoreth, the
        god of the Sidonians, to Chemosh, the god of Moab, and to Molech, the god
        of the Ammonites. They did not walk in my ways to do right in my eyes, my
        ordinances, or my judgments, as did David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But I will not take all of the kingdom from his hand, but I will
        make him a leader all the days of his life for the sake of David my servant
        whom I chose, who kept my commandments and my ordinances. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But I will take the kingship from the hand of his son, and I will
        give ten tribes to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'To his son I will give one tribe in order to be a lamp for my servant
        David, always before my face, in Jerusalem the city in which I have chosen
        to place my name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You I will take, and you shall reign over all your soul desires,
        and you shall be king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'It shall be that if you listen to all that I command you and you
        walk in my ways and you do right in my eyes by keeping my statutes and my
        commandments, as David my servant did, then I will be with you, and I will
        build an enduring house for you as I built for David, and I will give Israel
        to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "I will punish the offspring of David on account of this; however,
        not always.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Then Solomon sought to kill Jeroboam, but Jeroboam got up and fled
        to Egypt, to Shishak the king of Egypt, and he remained in Egypt until the
        death of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon and all that he did and his wisdom;
        are they not written on the scroll of the acts of Solomon? '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'All the days that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all of Israel
        were forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Then Solomon slept with his ancestors, and they buried him in the
        city of David his father, and Rehoboam his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Appeal to Rehoboam"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Appeal to Rehoboam"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all of Israel had come to Shechem
        to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It happened that Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard of it while he was
        still in Egypt where he had fled from the face of King Solomon, and Jeroboam
        had lived in Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they sent and summoned him, and Jeroboam and all the assembly
        of Israel came. Then they spoke to Rehoboam, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYour father made our yoke heavy; now lighten the hard labor
        of your father and the heavy yoke which he placed on us, and we will serve
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Rehoboam Seeks Counsel to Respond'
      title: Rehoboam Seeks Counsel to Respond
      number: 5
      content: "He said, \u201CGo up for three days and then return to me\u201D;
        so the people went away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then King Rehoboam consulted with the old men who had been serving
        before Solomon his father when he was alive, saying, \u201CHow are you advising
        me to answer this people?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They said to him, \u201CIf you will be a servant today to this people,
        then you will serve them; and if you answer them and speak good words to
        them, they will always be your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But he rejected the advice of the old men, which they gave him, and
        he consulted with the youngsters who had grown up with him, who were serving
        before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to them, \u201CWhat are you advising that we should reply
        to this people who spoke to me by saying, \u2018Lighten the yoke your father
        put on us.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the youngsters who had grown up with him spoke to him, saying,
        \u201CThus you shall say to this people who spoke to you: \u2018Your father
        made our yoke heavy, but you lighten it for us,\u2019 you shall say to them,
        \u2018My little finger is thicker than my father\u2019s loins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Rehoboam Responds Unwisely with Disastrous Results'
      title: Rehoboam Responds Unwisely with Disastrous Results
      number: 11
      content: "So then, my father loaded a heavy yoke on all of you, but I will
        add to your yoke; my father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline
        you with scorpions!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jeroboam and all of the people came to Rehoboam on the third day,
        as the king had spoken: \u201CReturn to me on the third day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the king answered all the people harshly, as he had rejected
        the advice of the old men that they had offered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He spoke to them according to the advice of the youngsters, saying,
        \u201CMy father made your yoke heavy, but I will add onto your yoke; my father
        disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the king did not listen to the people, for it was a turning of
        events from Yahweh in order to fulfill his word which Yahweh had spoken through
        the hand of Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When all of Israel saw that the king would not listen to them, the
        people answered the king, saying, \u201CWhat share do we have in David? There
        is no inheritance in the son of Jesse. To your tents, Israel! Now look to
        your house, David!\u201D Then Israel went to their tents. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The Israelites were living in the cities of Judah, and Rehoboam was
        reigning over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'King Rehoboam sent Adoram who was over the forced labor, and all
        of Israel cast stones at him and he died, but King Rehoboam managed to get
        up on the chariot to flee to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Civil War Averted'
      title: Civil War Averted
      number: 19
      content: 'So Israel rebelled against the house of David until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It happened that just when all of Israel heard that Jeroboam had
        returned, they sent and called him to the assembly and made him king over
        all of Israel. Not one followed after the house of David except the tribe
        of Judah alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled all of the house of
        Judah and the tribe of Benjamin, a hundred and eighty thousand choice troops
        to fight with the house of Israel, to restore the kingship to Rehoboam the
        son of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the word of God came to Shemaiah the man of God, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CSay to Rehoboam the son of Solomon the king of Judah and to
        all the house of Judah and Benjamin and the remainder of the people, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Jeroboam Becomes King over Israel'
      title: Jeroboam Becomes King over Israel
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Thus says Yahweh: \u201CYou shall not go up and you shall not
        fight with your brothers the Israelites. Return each of you to his house,
        for this thing was from me.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D So they heeded
        the word of Yahweh, and they returned to go home according to the word of
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Jeroboam built Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and he
        resided in it. Then he went out from there and built Penuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Jeroboam said to himself, \u201CNow the kingdom will return
        to the house of David "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "if this people go up to offer sacrifices in the house of Yahweh in
        Jerusalem. The heart of this people will return to their master Rehoboam
        the king of Judah, and they shall kill me and return to him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And the king had decided, so he made two golden calves and he said
        to them, \u201CYou have been going up to Jerusalem long enough; here are
        your gods, O Israel, who brought you up from the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He put one in Bethel, and the other he put in Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'This thing became a sin, and the people walked before the one as
        far as Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then he built the houses on the high places, and he appointed priests
        from all walks of life who were not from the sons of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Jeroboam also inaugurated a religious feast in the eighth month on
        the fifteenth day of the month, like the religious feast which was in Judah,
        and he offered sacrifices on the altar. Thus he did in Bethel, by sacrificing
        to the calves that he had made; and he placed in Bethel the priests of the
        high places which he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He offered sacrifices on the altar which he had made in Bethel on
        the fifteenth day of the eighth month which his heart had devised. He inaugurated
        a religious feast for the Israelites, and he went up to the altar to offer
        incense. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Man of God Proclaims Judgment against the False Altar'
      title: A Man of God Proclaims Judgment against the False Altar
      number: 1
      content: 'Suddenly a man of God from Judah came to Bethel, by the word of Yahweh,
        while Jeroboam was standing at the altar to offer incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he proclaimed against the altar by the word of Yahweh and said,
        \u201CO altar, altar, thus says Yahweh: \u2018Look, a son will be born to
        the house of David, Josiah by name, and he shall sacrifice on you the priests
        of the high places who burn incense on you, and human bones shall burn on
        you.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He gave a sign on that day, saying, \u201CThis is the sign that Yahweh
        has predetermined: Look, this altar will be torn apart, and the ashes that
        are on it will be poured out.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It happened at the moment the king heard the word of the man of God
        that he cried out against the altar in Bethel, Jeroboam stretched out his
        hand from the altar, saying, \u201CSeize him!\u201D But his hand which he
        stretched out to him was paralyzed, and he was not able to draw it back to
        himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the altar was torn apart and the ashes from the altar poured
        out according to the sign which the man of God had announced by the word
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king responded and said to the man of God, \u201CPlease
        entreat the favor of Yahweh your God, and pray for me that my hand may return
        to me.\u201D So the man of God entreated the face of Yahweh, and the hand
        of the king returned to him, as it was in the beginning. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the king spoke to the man of God, \u201CCome with me to the
        house and refresh yourself, that I may give you a gift.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the man of God said to the king, \u201CEven if you give to me
        half of your house I will not come with you, nor will I eat bread or drink
        water in this place, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "for the word of Yahweh has commanded me, saying, \u2018You shall
        not eat bread nor drink water, and you shall not return on the way that you
        came.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Man of God Disobeys'
      title: The Man of God Disobeys
      number: 10
      content: 'So he went another way, and he did not return by the way on which
        he had come to Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now a certain older prophet was living in Bethel, and his son came
        and recounted to him all of the things that the man of God had done that
        day in Bethel and the words he had spoken to the king, and they told them
        to their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then their father asked them, \u201CWhich way did he go?\u201D His
        sons had seen the way which the man of God who had come from Judah had taken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then he said to his sons, \u201CSaddle the donkey for me.\u201D So
        they saddled the donkey for him, and he mounted it "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and went after the man of God. He found him sitting under the oak
        and said to him, \u201CAre you the man of God who came from Judah?\u201D
        He said, \u201CI am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CCome with me to the house and eat some
        food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI am not able to return with you or to go with
        you. I will not eat food nor will I drink water with you in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For a word came to me by the word of Yahweh, \u2018You shall not
        eat food, nor shall you drink water there. You shall not return to go by
        the way that you came.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI am also a prophet like you. An angel spoke
        to me by the word of Yahweh, saying, \u2018Let him return with you to your
        house that he may eat food and drink water.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D He lied to
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So he returned with him and ate food in his house and drank water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now it happened that they were sitting at the table, and the word
        of Yahweh came to the prophet who brought him back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He proclaimed to the man of God who came from Judah, saying, \u201CThus
        says Yahweh: \u2018Because you have disobeyed the word of Yahweh and have
        not kept the command which Yahweh your God commanded you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Disobedient Man of God Dies'
      title: The Disobedient Man of God Dies
      number: 22
      content: "but you have returned and have eaten food and drank water in the
        place which he ordered you not to eat food nor to drink water, then your
        dead body shall not return to the tomb of your ancestors.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'It happened after he ate food and drank water that he saddled the
        donkey for the prophet whom he had brought back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When he left, a lion found him on the road and killed him, and his
        dead body was thrown on the road with the donkey standing beside it, and
        the lion was standing by the dead body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'As men were passing by and they saw the dead body thrown in the road
        and the lion standing beside the dead body, they came and told it in the
        city where the old prophet was living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When the prophet who had brought him back from the way heard, he
        said, \u201CIt is the man of God who disobeyed the mouth of Yahweh, and Yahweh
        has given him to the lion. He tore him in pieces and killed him according
        to the word of Yahweh which he had spoken to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then he spoke to his sons, saying, \u201CSaddle the donkey for me.\u201D
        So they saddled it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He went and found his dead body thrown in the road and a donkey with
        the lion standing beside it, but the lion had not eaten the corpse nor attacked
        the donkey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So the prophet lifted up the corpse of the man of God and put it
        on the donkey and brought it back. He came to the city of the old prophet
        to mourn him and to bury him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He put his corpse in his tomb, and they mourned over him, \u201CAlas,
        my brother!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "It happened after he buried him that he said to his sons, \u201CWhen
        I die, you shall bury me in the tomb where the man of God is buried; you
        shall lay my bones beside his bones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Jeroboam Continues in His Sin'
      title: Jeroboam Continues in His Sin
      number: 32
      content: "For surely, the thing which he proclaimed by the word of Yahweh against
        the altar which is in Bethel will happen, as it will against all the houses
        of the high places which are in the cities of Samaria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'After this event, Jeroboam did not turn from his evil way, but he
        returned and again made priests for the high places of people from all walks
        of life. He filled his hand with all his desire and became one of the priests
        of the high places himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'This matter became sin in the house of Jeroboam, to make it disappear
        and to destroy it from the surface of the earth. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment for Jeroboam Continues'
      title: Judgment for Jeroboam Continues
      number: 1
      content: 'At that time, Abijah son of Jeroboam became ill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jeroboam said to his wife, \u201CPlease get up and disguise yourself
        so that they will not know that you are the wife of Jeroboam, and go to Shiloh.
        Look, Ahijah the prophet is there, and he spoke concerning me before I became
        king over this people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You must take ten loaves of bread in your hand and cakes and a jar
        of honey, and you must go to him. He shall tell you what will happen to the
        boy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The wife of Jeroboam did so. She got up, went to Shiloh, and came
        to the house of Ahijah. Now Ahijah was not able to see, for his eyes were
        fixed because of his old age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Ahijah, \u201CLook, the wife of Jeroboam is coming
        to seek a word from you about her son, for he is ill. Thus and so you shall
        say to her. When she comes, she will be disguising herself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "It happened at the moment Ahijah heard the sound of her footsteps
        coming through the doorway, he said, \u201CCome in, wife of Jeroboam. Why
        are you making yourself unrecognizable? I have been sent a hard message for
        you: "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Go, tell Jeroboam, \u2018Thus says Yahweh the God of Israel: \u201CBecause
        I raised you from the midst of the people and I made you leader over my people
        Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I tore the kingdom from the house of David and I gave it to you.
        But you were not like my servant David who kept my commandments, and who
        went after me with all his heart, to do only what is right in my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But you did more evil than all who were before you. You have gone
        and made for yourself other gods and molten idols to provoke me, but me you
        have completely disregarded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore, look, I am about to bring disaster upon the house of Jeroboam,
        and I will cut off males from Jeroboam, bond or free, in Israel. I will burn
        after the house of Jeroboam as one burns after the manure, until it is finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He who dies for Jeroboam in the city, the dogs will eat. He who dies
        in the open field, the birds from the heavens will eat, for Yahweh has spoken
        it.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As for you, get up. Go to your house. When your feet enter the city,
        the child will die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'All of Israel will mourn for him, and they will bury him. This one
        alone will come to a tomb for Jeroboam, because a good thing has been found
        in him by Yahweh the God of Israel in the house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Yahweh will raise up a king for himself over Israel who will even
        now cut off the house of Jeroboam this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yahweh will strike Israel as one shakes the reed plant in the water,
        and he will root Israel up from this good land that he gave to their ancestors.
        He will scatter them beyond the River because they have made their sacred
        poles which are provoking Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He will give up Israel because of the sin of Jeroboam which he sinned
        and which he caused Israel to sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the wife of Jeroboam got up, went, and came to Tirzah. As she
        was coming to the threshold of the house, the boy died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They buried him and all of Israel mourned for him, according to the
        word of Yahweh which he had spoken by the hand of his servant Ahijah the
        prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Jeroboam, how he fought and how he reigned,
        behold, they are written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Rehoboam Reigns in Judah'
      title: Rehoboam Reigns in Judah
      number: 20
      content: 'The days which Jeroboam reigned were twenty-two years, and he slept
        with his ancestors. Then Nadab his son became king in place of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now Rehoboam the son of Solomon reigned in Judah. He was forty-one
        years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem,
        the city which, from all of the tribes of Israel, Yahweh chose to place his
        name. And the name of his mother was Naamah the Ammonitess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But Judah did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, and they annoyed him more
        than their fathers did with their sins that they had committed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They also built for themselves high places and stone pillars and
        sacred poles on every high hill and under every green tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Pharaoh Shishak of Egypt Raids Jerusalem'
      title: Pharaoh Shishak of Egypt Raids Jerusalem
      number: 24
      content: 'There were also male shrine prostitutes in the land, and they did
        according to all the abominations of the nations which Yahweh had driven
        out from before the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It happened in the fifth year of King Rehoboam that Shishak the king
        of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and he took the treasures of the house of Yahweh, and he took all
        the treasures of the king\u2019s house. He took the small gold shields that
        Solomon had made, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "so King Rehoboam made small copper shields in place of them and entrusted
        them to the commanders of the royal guard who keep the doorway of the king\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Whenever the king came to the house of Yahweh, the royal guard carried
        them and brought them back to the alcove room of the royal guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Rehoboam and all that he did, are they
        not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There was always war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then Rehoboam slept with his ancestors, and he was buried with his
        ancestors in the city of David. The name of his mother was Naamah the Ammonitess.
        Abijam his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Reign of Abijam in Judah'
      title: The Reign of Abijam in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam the son of Nebat, Abijam
        began to reign over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Three years he reigned in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Maacah
        the daughter of Abishalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He walked in all the sins of his father that he had done before him,
        and his heart was not fully with Yahweh his God as the heart of David his
        father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the sake of David, Yahweh his God gave him a lamp in Jerusalem,
        by establishing his son after him and by causing Jerusalem to exist; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "because David did right in the eyes of Yahweh and he didn\u2019t
        turn aside from all that he commanded him all the days of his life, except
        in the matter of Uriah the Hittite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Abijam and all that he did, are they
        not written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah?
        There was also war between Abijam and Jeroboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Reign of Asa in Judah'
      title: The Reign of Asa in Judah
      number: 8
      content: 'Abijam slept with his ancestors, and they buried him in the city
        of David, and Asa his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In the twentieth year of Jeroboam the king of Israel, Asa became
        the king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem, and the name of his mother
        was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Asa did right in the eyes of Yahweh, like David his ancestor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He put away the male shrine prostitutes from the land, and he removed
        all of the idols that his ancestors made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Also, he had Maacah his mother removed from the office of queen mother,
        as she had made a repulsive image for the Asherah. Asa also cut down her
        repulsive image and burned it in the Wadi Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the high places he did not remove. Nevertheless, the heart of
        Asa was completely with Yahweh all of his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He brought the holy objects of his father and his own holy objects
        to the house of Yahweh, silver and gold and utensils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'There was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all of their
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah, and he built Ramah to
        hinder the coming and going of anyone to Asa king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Asa took all of the silver and gold remaining in the storerooms of
        the house of Yahweh and in the treasury rooms of the house of the king, and
        he gave them into the hand of his servants; so King Asa sent them to Ben-Hadad
        the son of Tabrimmon the son of Hezion, the king of Aram, who lived in Damascus,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CLet there be a covenant between me and you, between my father
        and your father. Look, I have sent you a gift of silver and gold. Go, break
        your covenant with Baasha king of Israel that he may go up away from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Ben-Hadad listened to King Asa, and he sent the commanders of his
        armies against the cities of Israel and he attacked Ijon, Dan, Abel-Beth-Maacah,
        and all of Kinnereth, in addition to all the land of Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Baasha heard, he stopped building Ramah, and he lived in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then King Asa proclaimed among all of Israel that there was no one
        free from obligation, so they carried the stones of Ramah and its wood with
        which Baasha had built, and King Asa rebuilt Geba in Benjamin with them,
        and the Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Asa, all of his achievements, all that
        he did, and the cities which he built, are they not written in the scroll
        of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? But at the time of his old
        age, he developed a foot disease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Reign of Nadab in Israel'
      title: The Reign of Nadab in Israel
      number: 24
      content: 'Asa slept with his ancestors and was buried with his ancestors in
        the city of David his ancestor; Jehoshaphat his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Nadab the son of Jeroboam began to reign over Israel in the second
        year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, and he walked in the way of his
        father and in his sin that he caused Israel to commit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Baasha son of Ahijah of the house of Issachar conspired against him,
        and Baasha struck him down at Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines.
        Now Nadab and all of Israel were laying siege to Gibbethon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and Baasha killed him in the third year of Asa the king of Judah,
        and he reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'It happened that as soon as he became king, he killed all of the
        house of Jeroboam. There was no one left of Jeroboam who breathed, until
        he had destroyed him according to the word of Yahweh that he had spoken by
        the hand of his servant, Ahijah the Shilonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'because of the sins of Jeroboam that he had committed and that he
        had caused Israel to commit and because of his anger with which he had provoked
        Yahweh the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The Reign of Baasha in Israel'
      title: The Reign of Baasha in Israel
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Nadab and all that he did, are they
        not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'There was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha son of Ahijah had
        become king over all of Israel; he lived in Tirzah twenty-four years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, and he walked in the way of Jeroboam
        and in his sin that he caused Israel to commit. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' The word of Yahweh came to Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBecause I exalted you from the dust and I made you a leader
        over my people Israel, but you have walked in the way of Jeroboam and you
        caused my people Israel to sin, to provoke me with their sins, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I am now about to consume Baasha and his house. I will make your
        house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Those who die for Baasha in the city, the dogs will eat; those who
        die for him in the field, the birds of the heavens will eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Baasha, what he did, and his powerful
        deeds, are they not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the
        kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Baasha slept with his ancestors and was buried in Tirzah, and Elah
        his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Reign of Elah in Israel'
      title: The Reign of Elah in Israel
      number: 7
      content: 'Moreover, the word of Yahweh came to Baasha and to his house by the
        hand of Jehu the son of Hanani the prophet, because of all the evil that
        he did in the eyes of Yahweh by provoking him with the work of his hands,
        by being like the house of Jeroboam; and he destroyed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha
        became king over Israel for two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'His servant Zimri the commander of half of the chariots conspired
        against him. Now he had been in Tirzah drinking himself drunk in the house
        of Arza who was over the palace in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Zimri came and struck him down and killed him in the twenty-seventh
        year of Asa king of Judah and became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'It happened that as soon as he became king, at the moment he sat
        on his throne, he killed all of the house of Baasha. He left no males among
        his kindred or any of his friends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Zimri destroyed all of the house of Baasha according to the word
        of Yahweh which he spoke against Baasha by the hand of Jehu the prophet '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'because of all the sins of Baasha and the sins of Elah his son which
        they committed and which they caused Israel to sin by provoking Yahweh the
        God of Israel with their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Very Brief Reign of Zimri in Israel'
      title: The Very Brief Reign of Zimri in Israel
      number: 14
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Elah and all that he did, are they not
        written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned seven
        days in Tirzah. Now the army was encamping against Gibbethon which belonged
        to the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The encamping army heard that Zimri had conspired and moreover had
        killed the king, so they made Omri the commander of the army of Israel king
        over all Israel in the camp on that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Omri went up and all Israel with him from Gibbethon, and they
        besieged Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It happened that when Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went
        to the citadel fortress of the house of the king, and he burnt the house
        of the king over him with fire so that he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'This happened because of his sin which he committed by doing evil
        in the eyes of Yahweh, by going the way of Jeroboam and in his sin which
        he did by causing Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Reign of Omri in Israel'
      title: The Reign of Omri in Israel
      number: 20
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Zimri and his conspiracy which he made,
        are they not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings
        of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'At that time, the people of Israel were divided into two parts: half
        of the people went after Tibni the son of Ginath to make him king, and the
        other half went after Omri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The people who went after Omri overcame the people who went after
        Tibni the son of Ginath, so that he died and Omri became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri became king over
        Israel for twelve years. He reigned in Tirzah six years, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'then bought the hill of Samaria from Shemer for two talents of silver,
        fortified the hill, and called the name of the city Samaria that he built
        after Shemer, the owner of the hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But Omri did evil in the eyes of Yahweh more than all who were before
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He went in all the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat and in his sins
        that he caused Israel to sin by provoking Yahweh the God of Israel with their
        idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Omri that he did and his powerful deeds,
        are they not written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings
        of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Reign of Ahab in Israel'
      title: The Reign of Ahab in Israel
      number: 28
      content: 'Omri slept with his ancestors, and he was buried in Samaria, and
        Ahab his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now Ahab son of Omri became king over Israel in the thirty-eighth
        year of Asa king of Judah. Ahab son of Omri reigned over Israel in Samaria
        twenty-two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But Ahab son of Omri did evil in the eyes of Yahweh more than all
        who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "If it wasn\u2019t enough that he went after the sins of Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat, he also took as wife Jezebel the daughter of Ethbaal the
        king of the Sidonians. He went and served Baal and bowed down to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he built an altar to Baal in the house of Baal which he had built
        in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Ahab also made the sacred pole, and he continued to provoke Yahweh
        the God of Israel more than all the kings of Israel who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'In his days, Hiel the Bethelite rebuilt Jericho; at the cost of Abiram
        his firstborn he laid its foundation, and at the cost of Segub his younger
        sibling, he set up its gates, according to the word of Yahweh which he spoke
        by the hand of Joshua the son of Nun. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Prophet Elijah Arises'
      title: The Prophet Elijah Arises
      number: 1
      content: "Elijah the Tishbite from Tishbe of Gilead said to Ahab, \u201CAs
        Yahweh lives, the God of Israel before whom I stand, there shall surely not
        be dew nor rain these years except by my command.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the word of Yahweh came to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CGo from this place and turn to the east; you must hide yourself
        in the Wadi Kerith which faces the Jordan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It shall be that you shall drink from the wadi, and I have commanded
        the crows to sustain you there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So he went and did according to the word of Yahweh. He went and stayed
        in the Wadi Kerith which faces the Jordan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The crows were bringing bread and meat in the morning for him and
        bread and meat in the evening, and he drank from the wadi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It happened after a while that the wadi dried up, because there was
        no rain in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of Yahweh came to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CGet up and go to Zarephath which belongs to Sidon and stay
        there. Look, I have commanded a woman there, a widow, to sustain you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he arose and went to Zarephath and came to the gate of the city.
        There was a widow woman gathering wood, so he called to her, and he said,
        \u201CPlease bring a little water for me in a vessel so that I can drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "She went to fetch it, and he called to her and said, \u201CPlease
        bring me a morsel of bread in your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "She said, \u201CAs Yahweh your God lives, surely I do not have a
        cake, but only a handful of flour in the jar and a little olive oil in the
        jug. Here I am gathering a few pieces of wood, and I will go and prepare
        it for me and my son, that we might eat it and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Elijah said to her, \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid. Go and do according
        to your word; only make for me a small bread cake from it first, and bring
        it out to me. Make it for yourself and for your son afterward. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u2018The jar of flour will
        not be emptied and the jug of olive oil will not run out until the day Yahweh
        gives rain on the surface of the earth.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So she went and did according to the word of Elijah; then both she
        and he ate with her household for many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The jar of flour was not emptied and the jug of olive oil did not
        run out, according to the word of Yahweh which he spoke by the hand of Elijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It happened after these things that the son of the woman, the mistress
        of the house, became ill; and his illness was very severe until there was
        no breath left in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "She said to Elijah, \u201CWhat do you have against me, O man of God,
        that you have come to me to make known my guilt and to cause my son to die?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he said to her, \u201CGive me your son.\u201D He took him from
        her lap and carried him up to the upper room where he was staying, and he
        laid him on his bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he called to Yahweh and said, \u201CO Yahweh my God, are you
        also causing evil to come upon the widow with whom I am dwelling as an alien
        by causing her son to die?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He stretched himself out on the child three times and called to Yahweh
        and said, \u201CO Yahweh my God, please let the life of this child return
        within him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yahweh listened to the voice of Elijah, and the life of the child
        returned within him, and he lived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Elijah then took the child and brought him down from the upper room
        to the house and gave him to his mother. Elijah said, \u201CLook, your son
        is alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the woman said to Elijah, \u201CNow this I know, that you are
        a man of God and the word of Yahweh in your mouth is truth.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: War between Elijah and the Prophets of Baal'
      title: War between Elijah and the Prophets of Baal
      number: 1
      content: "It happened many days later that the word of Yahweh came to Elijah
        in the third year, saying, \u201CGo, present yourself to Ahab so that I may
        give rain on the surface of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Elijah went to present himself to Ahab. Now the famine was severe
        in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Ahab summoned Obadiah who was over the house. (Now Obadiah was fearing
        Yahweh greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It had happened that when Jezebel killed the prophets of Yahweh,
        Obadiah took a hundred prophets and hid them by fifties in the cave and sustained
        them with food and water.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Ahab said to Obadiah, \u201CGo through the land to all the springs
        of water and to all the wadis. Perhaps we may find green grass that we may
        keep horses and mules alive and that we might not lose any of the animals.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they divided the land for themselves in order to pass through
        it; Ahab went one way by himself, and Obadiah went another way by himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It happened that Obadiah was on the way, and suddenly Elijah was
        there to meet him. When he recognized him, he fell on his face and said,
        \u201CIs this you, my lord Elijah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He said to him, \u201CI am. Go, say to your lord, \u2018Elijah is
        here.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said, \u201CHow have I sinned that you are giving your servant
        into the hand of Ahab to kill me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As Yahweh your God lives, surely there is not a nation or a kingdom
        to which my lord has not sent me to seek you. If they would say, \u2018He
        is not here,\u2019 then he would make the kingdom or the nation swear that
        it could not find you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now you are saying, \u2018Go, say to your lord: \u201CElijah is here.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And it will happen that I will go from you and the Spirit of Yahweh
        will carry you up to where I do not know. Then I will come to tell Ahab,
        but he will not find you, and then he will kill me, even though your servant
        has feared Yahweh from my youth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Has it not been told to my lord what I did when Jezebel killed the
        prophets of Yahweh? I hid a hundred men of the prophets of Yahweh by fifties
        in the cave, and I sustained them with food and water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now you are saying, \u2018Go, say to your lord: \u201CElijah is here,\u201D&nbsp;\u2019
        and he will kill me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Elijah said, \u201CAs Yahweh of hosts lives, before whom I stand,
        I will certainly show myself to him today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Obadiah went to meet Ahab, and he told him, so Ahab went to meet
        Elijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Ahab saw Elijah, Ahab said to him, \u201CIs this you who throws
        Israel into confusion?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He said, \u201CI did not throw Israel into confusion; rather you
        and the house of your father have by forsaking the commands of Yahweh when
        you went after the Baals! "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So then, send word and assemble all of Israel to me on Mount Carmel,
        with the four hundred and fifty prophets of Baal and the four hundred prophets
        of Asherah, who eat at the table of Jezebel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Ahab sent word among the Israelites, and he assembled the prophets
        to Mount Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Elijah approached to all the people and said, \u201CHow long will
        you go limping over two opinions? If Yahweh is God, go after him; but if
        Baal, go after him.\u201D But the people did not answer him a word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Elijah said to the people, \u201CI alone am left a prophet of
        Yahweh, but the prophets of Baal are four hundred and fifty men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Let them give us two bulls, and let them choose for themselves one
        bull, cut him in pieces, and put it on the wood, but don\u2019t let them
        start a fire on it. I will prepare the other bull and set it on the wood,
        but I will put no fire on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then you call on the name of your god, and I will call on the name
        of Yahweh, and it shall be that the god who answers by fire, he is God.\u201D
        Then all the people answered and said, \u201CThe word is good!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, \u201CChoose for yourselves
        one bull and prepare it first, for you are the majority, and call on the
        name of your god, but don\u2019t set fire under it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So they took the bull that he allowed to them, prepared it, and called
        upon the name of Baal from morning until noon, saying, \u201CO Baal, answer
        us!\u201D But there was no voice and there was no answer, so they limped
        about the altar which they had made. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "It happened at noon that Elijah mocked them and said, \u201CCall
        out with a loud voice, for he is a god! Perhaps he is meditating, or is using
        the bathroom, or is on a journey. Perhaps he is asleep and must wake up!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So they called out with a loud voice, and they cut themselves with
        swords and with spears as was their custom, until the blood poured out over
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'It happened as noon passed, they raged until the time of the evening
        offering, but there was no voice, there was no answer, and no one paid attention. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Elijah said to all the people, \u201CCome near to me,\u201D
        so all the people came closer to him. He repaired the altar of Yahweh that
        had been destroyed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Elijah took twelve stones according to the number of the tribes of
        the sons of Jacob, to whom the word of God came, saying, \u201CIsrael shall
        be your name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'With them, he built an altar in the name of Yahweh, and he made a
        trench which would have held about two seahs of seed, all around the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And he arranged the wood, cut the bull into pieces, and placed it
        on the wood. Then he said, \u201CFill four jars with water, and pour it on
        the burnt offering and on the wood.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He said, \u201CDo it again!\u201D They did it again. He said, \u201CDo
        it a third time!\u201D So they did it a third time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The water went all around the altar, and the trench also was filled
        with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "It happened at the offering of the evening oblation, Elijah the prophet
        went near, and he said, \u201CO Yahweh, God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel;
        let it be known today that you are God in Israel and that I am your servant
        and that I have done all of these things by your words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Answer me, O Yahweh, answer me; that this people may know that you,
        O Yahweh, are God and that you have turned their hearts back again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then the fire of Yahweh fell, and it consumed the burnt offering,
        and the wood, and the stones, and the dust; and the water which was in the
        trench it licked up! '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When all the people saw, they fell on their faces and said, \u201CYahweh,
        he is God! Yahweh, he is God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then Elijah said to them, \u201CSeize the prophets of Baal; don\u2019t
        let any man of them escape!\u201D So they seized them, and Elijah brought
        them down to the wadi of Kishon and killed them there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then Elijah said to Ahab, \u201CGo up, eat and drink, for there is
        the sound of the noise of rain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So Ahab went up to eat and to drink while Elijah went to the top
        of Carmel, bent down to the earth, and put his face between his knees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then he said to his servant, \u201CPlease go and look in the direction
        of the sea.\u201D So he went up and looked; then he said, \u201CThere is
        nothing.\u201D Then he said, \u201CGo back,\u201D seven times. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "It happened that at the seventh time, he said, \u201CLook, there
        is a small cloud, as the hand of a man, coming up from the sea.\u201D Then
        Elijah said, \u201CGo up, say to Ahab, \u2018Harness your horses and go down,
        lest the rain stop you.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'In no time the heavens grew black with clouds and wind, and there
        was heavy rain. Ahab rode and he went to Jezreel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'but the hand of Yahweh was on Elijah; he girded up his loins and
        ran before Ahab as one comes to Jezreel. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Flees to Horeb'
      title: Elijah Flees to Horeb
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done and how he had killed
        all the prophets with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah, saying, \u201CThus may the
        gods do to me, and may they add to it, surely at this time tomorrow I will
        make your life as the life of one of them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then he became afraid, got up, and fled for his life. He came to
        Beersheba which belongs to Judah, and he left his servant there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then he went into the wilderness one day\u2019s journey, and he went
        and sat under a certain broom tree. Then he asked Yahweh that he might die,
        and he said, \u201CIt is enough now, Yahweh; take my life, for I am no better
        than my ancestors.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He lay down and fell asleep under a certain broom tree, and suddenly
        this angel was touching him and said to him, \u201CGet up, eat!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He looked, and behold, a bread cake on hot coals was near his head
        and a jar of water, so he ate and drank. Then he did it again and lay down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The angel of Yahweh appeared a second time and touched him and said,
        \u201CGet up, eat, for the journey is greater than you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Elijah Encounters Yahweh at Horeb'
      title: Elijah Encounters Yahweh at Horeb
      number: 8
      content: 'So he got up, ate, drank, and went in the strength of that food forty
        days and forty nights up to Horeb, the mountain of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He came to the cave there and spent the night there. Suddenly the
        word of Yahweh came to him and asked him, \u201CElijah, what are you doing
        here?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI have been very zealous for Yahweh the God of
        hosts, for the Israelites have forsaken your covenant. They have demolished
        your altars, and they have killed your prophets with the sword. I alone am
        left over, and they seek to take my life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said, \u201CGo out and stand on the mountain before Yahweh.\u201D
        Suddenly Yahweh was passing by, with a great and strong wind ripping the
        mountains and crushing rocks before Yahweh; but Yahweh was not in the wind.
        After the wind, there was an earthquake; but Yahweh was not in the earthquake. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'After the earthquake was a fire, but Yahweh was not in the fire.
        After the fire there was the sound of a gentle whisper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "It happened at the moment Elijah heard, he covered his face with
        his cloak and went out and stood at the entrance of the cave. Suddenly a
        voice came to him and said, \u201CElijah, why are you here?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He said, \u201CI have been very zealous for Yahweh the God of Hosts,
        for the Israelites have forsaken your covenant, demolished your altars, and
        killed your prophets with the sword; I alone am left, and they seek to take
        my life!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Yahweh said to him, \u201CGo, return on your way to the wilderness
        of Damascus. Go and anoint Hazael as king over Aram; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Jehu son of Nimshi you shall anoint as king over Israel. You
        shall also anoint Elisha son of Shaphat from Abel-Meholah as prophet in your
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It shall be that the one who escapes from the sword of Hazael, Jehu
        will kill; the one who escapes from the sword of Jehu, Elisha shall kill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I will leave in Israel seven thousand, all of the knees that have
        not bowed down to Baal and all of the mouths that have not kissed him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So he went from there and found Elisha son of Shaphat while he was
        plowing with twelve pairs of oxen before him. When he and the twelve passed
        Elijah, he threw his cloak on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he left the oxen and ran after Elijah and said, \u201CPlease
        let me kiss my father and my mother, and then I will go after you.\u201D
        Then he said, \u201CGo, return, for what I have done to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So he returned from after him, and he took a pair of oxen and slaughtered
        them, and with the yoke of the oxen he boiled the flesh and gave it to the
        people and they ate. Then he arose and went after Elijah and served him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Syrian-Israeli Conflicts: Ben-Hadad vs. Ahab of Israel'
      title: 'Syrian-Israeli Conflicts: Ben-Hadad vs. Ahab of Israel'
      number: 1
      content: 'Ben-Hadad king of Aram gathered all of his army, and thirty-two kings
        were with him, and horses and chariots. He went up and laid siege against
        Samaria and fought with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He sent messengers to the city to Ahab king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He said to him, \u201CThus says Ben-Hadad: \u2018Your silver and
        your gold are mine, and your women and your best sons are mine.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king of Israel answered and said, \u201CAs your word, my
        master the king; I am yours, and all that is mine is yours.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The messengers returned and said, \u201CThus says Ben-Hadad, saying,
        \u2018I sent to you saying, \u201CYour silver and gold are mine, and your
        women and your best sons you must give to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So at this time tomorrow, I will send my servants to you that they
        might search your house and the houses of your servants. All the desire of
        your eyes they will lay hands on and take it away.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the king of Israel called all the elders of the land and said,
        \u201CPlease know and realize that this man is seeking trouble, for he sent
        to me for my women, my sons, my silver, and my gold, and I did not withhold
        anything from him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All of the elders and all of the people said to him, \u201CDo not
        listen and do not consent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So he said to the messengers of Ben-Hadad, \u201CSay to my lord the
        king, \u2018All that you demanded from your servant at the first, I will
        do, but this thing I am not able to do.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D Then the messengers
        went and made a report to him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Ben-Hadad sent to him and said, \u201CThus may the gods do to
        me and thus may they add if the dust of Samaria is sufficient for the hollow
        of a hand for all of the people who are at my feet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The king of Israel answered and said, \u201CTell him, \u2018Let not
        him who girds on his armor boast as one who takes off his armor.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It happened at the moment he heard this word, he and the kings were
        drinking in the tents. He said to his servants, \u201CGet ready to attack.\u201D
        So they got ready to attack the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Suddenly a certain prophet approached Ahab king of Israel and said,
        \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Have you seen all this great crowd? Behold,
        I am giving it into your hand today, that you may know that I am Yahweh.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Ahab said, \u201CBy whom?\u201D And he said, \u201CThus says Yahweh:
        \u2018By the servants of the commanders of the provinces.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        He asked, \u201CWho will begin the battle?\u201D And he said, \u201CYou.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So he mustered the servants of the commanders of the provinces, and
        there were two hundred and thirty-two. After them he mustered all of the
        army, all the sons of Israel, seven thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They went out at noon while Ben-Hadad was drinking himself drunk
        in the tents, he and the thirty-two kings helping him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the servants of the commanders of the provinces went out first,
        and Ben-Hadad sent, and they reported to him, saying, \u201CMen have come
        out from Samaria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said, \u201CIf they have come out for peace, seize them alive;
        and if they have come out for war, seize them alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But these had come out from the city, the servants of the commanders
        of the provinces, and the army that was after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Each man killed his man, and the Arameans fled, so Israel pursued
        them, but Ben-Hadad king of Aram escaped on a horse with cavalry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The king of Israel went out and attacked the horses and the chariots
        and defeated Aram with a great blow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the prophet came near to the king of Israel, and he said to
        him, \u201CGo, strengthen yourself; consider well what you should do, for
        the king of Aram is coming against you at the turn of the year.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The servants of the king of Aram said to him, \u201CTheir gods are
        gods of the mountains, therefore they were stronger than we. Let us fight
        with them in the plain; surely we will be stronger than they. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Do this thing: remove the kings each from his post, and put a governor
        in their place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "You must muster an army for yourself as the army you have lost, and
        horses and chariots as the horses and chariots you lost, then we will fight
        them in the plain. Surely we will be stronger than they.\u201D So he listened
        to their voice and did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'It happened at the turning of the year that Ben-Hadad mustered Aram
        and went up to Aphek for the war with Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The Israelites had been mustered and provisioned, and they went to
        engage them. The Israelites encamped opposite them as two flocks of goats,
        but the Arameans filled the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the man of God approached, and he spoke to the king of Israel,
        and he said, \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Because Aram has said, \u201CYahweh
        is a god of the mountains and not a god of the valleys,\u201D&nbsp;\u2019
        I will give all this great crowd into your hand that you may know that I
        am Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These encamped opposite for seven days, and it happened on the seventh
        day that the battle began, and the Israelites killed the Arameans, one hundred
        thousand infantry in one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then those who remained fled to Aphek, to the city, and the wall
        fell on twenty-seven thousand men who had remained, so Ben-Hadad fled and
        went to the innermost rooms of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then his servants said to him, \u201CPlease now, we have heard that
        the kings of the house of Israel are kings of mercy. Let us now put sackcloth
        on around our waists and ropes on our heads. Then let us go out to the king
        of Israel. Perhaps he will let you live.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "So they tied sackcloth around their waists and ropes on their heads.
        Then they went to the king of Israel and said, \u201CYour servant Ben-Hadad
        says, \u2018Please let me live.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D And he said, \u201CIs my
        brother still alive?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The men took this as a good omen and they quickly accepted it as
        true from him, and they said, \u201CYour brother Ben-Hadad lives.\u201D So
        he said, \u201CGo, get him.\u201D Ben-Hadad came out to him, and Ahab pulled
        him up on the chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Ben-Hadad said to him, \u201CThe cities which my father took from
        your father I shall return. You may set up streets with stalls for yourself
        in Damascus just as my father set up in Samaria.\u201D Then Ahab said, \u201COn
        these terms I will let you go,\u201D So he made a covenant with him and let
        him go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "A certain man from the sons of the prophets said to his fellow countryman,
        \u201CBy the word of Yahweh, please strike me.\u201D But the man refused
        to strike him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "He said to him, \u201CBecause you have not obeyed the voice of Yahweh,
        look, as you now are going from me, a lion will kill you.\u201D When he went
        from beside him, the lion found him and killed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then he found another man and said, \u201CStrike me, please,\u201D
        so the man struck him sharply and wounded him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then the prophet went and waited for the king along the road and
        disguised himself with a headband over his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "As the king was passing by, he called to the king and said, \u201CYour
        servant went out in the thick of the battle, and suddenly a man turned and
        brought a man to me and said, \u2018Guard this man. If by any means he should
        be missed, it will be your life in his place, or you shall pay a talent of
        silver.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "It happened that your servant was busy here and there, and he disappeared.\u201D
        Then the king said to him, \u201CYour own judgment has been determined.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'He quickly removed the headband from his eyes, and the king of Israel
        recognized him, that he was from the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "He said to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Because you have let
        the man I devoted for destruction go from your hand, your life shall be in
        place of his life and your people in place of his people.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Then the king of Israel went to his house, sullen and angry, and
        he came to Samaria. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite'
      title: The Vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened after these things that Naboth the Jezreelite had a vineyard
        which was in Jezreel beside the palace of Ahab king of Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Ahab spoke to Naboth, saying, \u201CGive me your vineyard that it
        may be mine for a garden of vegetable plants, because it is near, beside
        my house, and I will give to you a better vineyard in place of it. If it
        is better in your eyes, I will give you the money of its price.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Naboth said to Ahab, \u201CFar be it from me from Yahweh that I should
        give the inheritance of my ancestors to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Ahab went to his house, sullen and angry because of the word
        that Naboth the Jezreelite had spoken to him when he had said, \u201CI will
        not give to you the inheritance of my ancestors.\u201D So he lay on his bed,
        turned away his face, and would not eat any food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jezebel his wife came to him, and she said to him, \u201CWhat
        is this, that your spirit is sullen and you are not eating food?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he said to her, \u201CWhen I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite
        and asked him, \u2018Give me your vineyard for money, or it you prefer, I
        will give you a vineyard in place of it,\u2019 he said, \u2018I will not
        give you my vineyard.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jezebel his wife said to him, \u201CNow, you rule over Israel. Get
        up, eat food, and let your heart be cheerful. I myself will give you the
        vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So she wrote letters in the name of Ahab and sealed them with his
        seal. She sent the letters to the elders and the nobles who were dwelling
        with Naboth in his city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She had written in the letters, saying, \u201CCall a fast and seat
        Naboth at the head of the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Seat two men, scoundrels, opposite him. Let them witness against
        him saying, \u2018You cursed God and the king.\u2019 Then you shall bring
        him out and stone him so that he dies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The men of his city and the elders and nobles who were living in
        his city did according to what Jezebel had sent to them, as was written in
        the letters which she had sent to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They called a fast, and they seated Naboth at the head of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the two men, scoundrels, came, sat opposite him, and the scoundrels
        witnessed against Naboth before the people, saying, \u201CNaboth cursed God
        and the king,\u201D so they brought him outside of the city and stoned him
        with stones, and he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They sent to Jezebel saying, \u201CNaboth has been stoned, and he
        is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "It happened at the moment Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned
        and died, Jezebel said to Ahab, \u201CGet up, take possession of the vineyard
        of Naboth the Jezreelite which he had refused to give to you for money, for
        Naboth is not alive, but dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Elijah Responds to Ahab'
      title: Elijah Responds to Ahab
      number: 16
      content: 'When Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, he got up to go down to the
        vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite to take possession of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The word of Yahweh came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CArise, go down to meet Ahab the king of Israel who is in Samaria.
        Look in the vineyard of Naboth, where he has gone to take possession of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You shall say to him, \u2018Thus says Yahweh: \u201CHave you committed
        murder and also taken possession?\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 You shall also say to
        him, \u2018Thus says Yahweh: \u201CIn the place where the dogs licked the
        blood of Naboth, the dogs will also lick your blood.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Ahab said to Elijah, \u201CHave you found me, my enemy?\u201D
        He said, \u201CI have found you because you have sold yourself to do evil
        in the eyes of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Look, I am bringing disaster on you, and I will sweep away
        after you. I will cut off for Ahab every male in Israel, bond or free. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat
        and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, because you made me angry
        and have caused Israel to sin.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Moreover, concerning Jezebel, Yahweh has said, \u2018The dogs will
        eat Jezebel in the outer rampart of Jezreel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The one who dies for Ahab in the city, the dogs will eat; the one
        who dies in the open country, the birds of heaven will eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Truly, there was no one like Ahab who had sold himself by doing evil
        in the eyes of Yahweh, whose wife Jezebel urged him on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Also, he acted very abominably by going after idols like all the
        Amorites had done whom Yahweh had driven out from before the Israelites.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When Ahab heard these words, he tore his clothes and put sackcloth
        over his flesh, fasted, lay in the sackcloth, and went about dejectedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then the word of Yahweh came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CHave you seen how Ahab has humbled himself before me? Because
        he has humbled himself before me, I will not bring disaster in his days.
        I will bring the disaster on his house in the days of his son.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoshaphat of Judah Allies with Ahab of Israel'
      title: Jehoshaphat of Judah Allies with Ahab of Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'They lived three years, and there was no war between Aram and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It happened in the third year, Jehoshaphat king of Judah went down
        to the king of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and the king of Israel said to his servants, \u201CDo you know Ramoth-Gilead
        belongs to us, and we are doing nothing about taking it from the hand of
        the king of Aram?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then he said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CWill you go with me to the battle
        for Ramoth-Gilead?\u201D Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, \u201CI
        am like you; my people are like your people; my horses are like your horses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jehoshaphat also said to the king of Israel, \u201CPlease inquire
        for the word of Yahweh today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king of Israel assembled the prophets, about four hundred
        men, and he said to them, \u201CShall I go against Ramoth-Gilead for the
        battle, or should I refrain?\u201D Then they said, \u201CGo up, for the Lord
        will give it into the hand of the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Jehoshaphat said, \u201CIs there no prophet of Yahweh here that
        we might still inquire from him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CThere is still
        one man to inquire from Yahweh, but I despise him, for he never prophesies
        anything good concerning me, but only bad: Micaiah the son of Imlah.\u201D
        Then Jehoshaphat said, \u201CThe king should not say so.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The king of Israel summoned a certain court official, and he said,
        \u201CQuickly fetch Micaiah son of Imlah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah were each sitting
        on his throne, dressed in their robes, at the threshing floor at the entrance
        of the gate of Samaria, with all the prophets prophesying before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Zedekiah son of Kenaanah made horns of iron for himself and said,
        \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018With these you shall gore the Arameans until
        finishing them.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "All of the prophets were likewise prophesying, saying, \u201CGo up
        to Ramoth-Gilead and triumph, and Yahweh will give it into the hand of the
        king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the messenger who had gone to summon Micaiah said to him, \u201CPlease
        now, the words of the prophet are unanimously favorable to the king. Please
        let your words be as one word with them, and speak favorably.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Micaiah said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, surely only as Yahweh speaks
        to me, that will I speak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When he came to the king, the king asked him, \u201CMicaiah, shall
        we go to Ramoth-Gilead to the battle, or shall we refrain?\u201D He said
        to him, \u201CGo up and triumph, and Yahweh will give it into the hand of
        the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the king said to him, \u201CHow many times must I make you swear
        that you shall not tell me anything but truth in the name of Yahweh?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So he said, \u201CI saw all of Israel scattering to the mountains,
        like the sheep without a shepherd. Yahweh also said, \u2018There are no masters
        for these, let them return in peace, each to his house.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CDid I not say
        to you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but disaster?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said, \u201CTherefore, hear the word of Yahweh. I saw Yahweh
        sitting on his throne with all the hosts of heaven standing beside him from
        his right hand and from his left hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Yahweh said, \u2018Who will entice Ahab so that he will go up
        and fall at Ramoth-Gilead?\u2019 Then this one was saying one thing and the
        other one was saying another.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then a spirit came out and stood before Yahweh and said, \u2018I
        will entice him,\u2019 and Yahweh said to him, \u2018How?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He said, \u2018I will go out and I will be a false spirit in the
        mouth of all his prophets.\u2019 And he said, \u2018You shall entice and
        succeed, go out and do so.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So then, see that Yahweh has placed a false spirit in the mouth of
        all of these your prophets, and Yahweh has spoken disaster concerning you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Zedekiah son of Kenaanah came near and slapped Micaiah on the
        cheek and said, \u201CWhen did the Spirit of Yahweh pass from me to speak
        with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Micaiah said, \u201CBehold, you are about to see on that day
        when you go from room to room to hide.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The king of Israel said, \u201CTake Micaiah and return him to Amon
        the commander of the city and to Jehoash the son of the king; "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the king: \u201CPut this fellow in the house
        of imprisonment and feed him reduced rations of food and water until I come
        in peace.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Micaiah said, \u201CIf you indeed return in peace, then Yahweh
        has not spoken with me.\u201D Then he said, \u201CLet all the peoples hear!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah went up to
        Ramoth-Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CI will disguise
        myself and go into the battle, but you wear your robes.\u201D So the king
        of Israel disguised himself, and he went into the battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The king of Aram commanded his thirty-two chariot commanders, saying,
        \u201CYou shall not fight with small or great, but only against the king
        of Israel, him alone!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When the chariot commanders saw Jehoshaphat, they said, \u201CSurely
        he is the king of Israel,\u201D and they turned to fight against him, so
        Jehoshaphat called out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When the chariot commanders saw that it was not the king of Israel,
        they turned away from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But another man drew his bow fully and struck the king of Israel
        between the armor scales and the breastplate; so he said to his chariot driver,
        \u201CTurn the chariot and bring me out from the camp, for I am wounded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The battle intensified on that day, and the king was being propped
        up in the chariot opposite Aram, but he died in the evening, and the blood
        of the wound ran out to the floor of the chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then the shout passed through the camp about sunset, saying, \u201CEach
        man to his city and each to his land!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So the king died, and they brought him to Samaria, and they buried
        the king in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They washed the chariot by the pool of Samaria, and the dogs licked
        his blood (now, the prostitutes washed themselves there) according to the
        word of Yahweh which he had spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Ahab and all that he did, and the ivory
        palace and all the cities that he built, are they not written in the scroll
        of the events of the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: King Jehoshaphat of Judah'
      title: King Jehoshaphat of Judah
      number: 40
      content: 'So Ahab slept with his ancestors, and Ahaziah his son became king
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Jehoshaphat the son of Asa became king over Judah in the fourth year
        of Ahab king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he became king, and he
        reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Azubah
        daughter of Shilhi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He walked in all of the way of Asa his father, and he did not turn
        aside from it, doing right in the eyes of Yahweh. Only he did not remove
        the high places; the people were still sacrificing and burning incense on
        the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: ' But, Jehoshaphat made peace with the king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Jehoshaphat, his powerful deeds he did,
        and how he fought, are they not written in the scroll of the events of the
        days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The remainder of the male shrine prostitutes who were left over in
        the days of Asa his father he exterminated from the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'There was not a king in Edom; a governor served as king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Jehoshaphat built ships of the Tarshish type to go to Ophir for the
        gold; but he did not go because the ships were destroyed at Ezion-Geber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Then Ahaziah son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CLet my servants
        go with your servants in the ships,\u201D but Jehoshaphat was not willing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: King Ahaziah of Israel'
      title: King Ahaziah of Israel
      number: 50
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat slept with his ancestors and was buried with his
        ancestors in the city of David his ancestor, and Joram his son became king
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Ahaziah son of Ahab became king over Israel in Samaria in the seventeenth
        year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, and he went in the way of his
        father and his mother and in the way of Jeroboam son of Nebat who caused
        Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'He served Baal and bowed down to him; and he provoked Yahweh the
        God of Israel according to all that his father did. '
      comments: []
